caption:
Explore V3 is an all-weather CE certified mesh riding jacket from Royal Enfield. The one I have is a full black colour one - my personal favourite. Compared to the Explore V2 version, the new upgrade has better protection with Knox MICRO-LOCK CE Level 2 protectors at elbow and shoulder and the jacket itself is CE certified. The jacket comes with a thermal liner and a rain jacket that can be worn as an inner or outer liner. The rain jacket fits in the back pocket of the jacket and so easily usable when it rains all suddenly. Fit of the jacket is also excellent and it’s very light. The only thing that I feel could have been better is the back protector - it feels quiet thin. Apart from that, Explore V3 is good for daily use and long distance rides.

Riding Gear: NH 44 Helmet • Explore V3 Jacket • Burnish Gloves • Royal Enfield x Levis Jeans

caption:
100% Shot on #GoProHERO9 Dust Explosion x Skateboarding 粉塵爆発xスケートボード with @kai.shimakage @gopro @goproanz @goprojp 
Done in a police attended sight. FYI We had no problem with the location, and we have cleaned well.
Powder is non-toxic, eco friendly, skin friendly, easily washable, and non flammable.
A dusk explosion is a phenomena of when non-flammable powder gets up in the air like dusts, the surface of the powder facing the oxygen increases, which results in explosion.
安全を考慮して行なっております。粉はもちろん不燃で環境にいいものを使用して、警察からもOKを頂いた監視元の環境で行なっております。真似はしないでください。粉塵爆発は燃えない粉や金属が宙に放散することで酸素に触れる面積が増えて燃える現象のことを言います。
この粉は自然に優しい商品であり、毒性は一切なく、簡単に水で落ちる不燃性のものです。
粉塵爆発の放散面積の計算はAvを放散面積(m2)とした場合、Av = (8.535×10-5)(1+1.75Pstat)KstV0.75{(1-Π)/Π}1/2〔m2〕
※ Π = Pred/Pmax
で求められ、今回使用しました粉は粒子径28[μm]であり9.4Pmax[x102kPa]、75Kst[x102kPa/m/s]、危険等級1Stです。現場には万が一を備え12Lの水と消火器を消火担当である第3者が備えておりました。

caption:
#BJsWholesalePartner Fall meals are my favorite to create, there’s just something about the 
warmth of cozy foods that brings me comfort. I want to share a yummy meal with you all, as a 
busy mom of 4 I want to make easy meals. Thanks to @BJsWholesale I can get everything I need 
in-club, online or even for pickup in-club. I was able to create this Chili-Bean Casserole just by 
going on the BJ’s app, ordering my ingredients and picking it up at a time convenient for my 
family and me. Be sure to go to my stories or click the link in my bio to shop and get the recipe 
card! #BJsSmartSaver #BJsWholesaleClub
Servings: 8 People 
Prep Time: 10 mins
Cook Time: 45 mins
Total Time: 55 mins 
1lb of Wellsley Farms Ground Beef 
2 8oz. cans tomato sauce

1 15oz. can kidney beans
1 15oz. can of corn
1 1.25oz. packet of chili seasoning
1 cup water
Cornbread Ingredients:
1/2 cup all-purpose flour
2 tbsp. Of Wellsley Farms Organic Cane Sugar
3/4 cup finely ground cornmeal
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 tsp. baking soda
2/3 cup buttermilk
1/4 cup Wellsley Farms Canola Oil
1 Wellsley Farms egg
Toppings: (optional)
Wellsley Farms Mexican Shredded Cheese
Wellsley Farms Sour Cream

Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. To start making the cornbread layer, mix all the cornbread ingredients into a medium mixing bowl and mix until smooth. Pour into an 8in pan and bake for 12-16 mins or until light brown. 
While cornbread is baking put the kidney beans and corn on medium heat. In a separate pan
brown hamburger meat. Once meat is brown, add chili powder, water, tomato sauce and 
simmer for 10 mins. Drain kidney beans and corn, add it to the hamburger meat, and mix 
everything together. Put the beans, hamburger and corn mixture on top of the cornbread, add cheese (optional) and bake another 5-10 mins or until cheese is melted. Once it’s had time to cool down cut and serve, please allow 10-15 mins to cool so that the cornbread has enough time to settle and not break apart.

caption:
When it gets cold out all I want to do is bake. I have loved baking for as long as I can remember. What is your favorite thing to bake? Thanks to @zulay_kitchen for #gifting me a 5 piece spatula set to make scraping down bowls and mixing a breeze. The spatulas  are silicon on the outside but have a sturdy stainless steel core. Use code happilyheatherj10 to save 10% on all your kitchen gaget needs. I included the recipe below for my oatmeal cookies 

1 cups all-purpose flour

2 teaspoons  cinnamon to taste

1/2 teaspoon baking soda

1/4 teaspoon salt

1/2 cup unsalted butter softened to room temperature

1/2 cup packed brown sugar

1/4 cup granulated sugar

1 large egg

1 tablespoon honey

2 teaspoons vanilla

1 and 1/2 cups oatmeal 

2/3 cup raisins

Instructions

In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.

In a large bowl using an electric mixer, beat together the butter, brown sugar and white sugar until fluffy (about 2 minutes).

Beat in the honey, vanilla extract and egg.

With the mixer on low speed, beat the flour mixture into the butter mixture.

Mix in the oats, followed by the raisins. The dough will be sticky.

Cover the bowl with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes or overnight.

When ready to bake, preheat the oven to 350F degrees. Line 2 cookie sheets with parchment paper.

Using a cookie scoop or tablespoon, form the dough into balls of about 1 to 2 tablespoons and place 2 inches apart on the lined cookie sheets.

Bake 1 tray at a time, on the middle rack of the oven for 9-11 minutes or until the tops look just set. 

Remove from the oven and cool fully on the cookie tray.

caption:
Quem me acompanha nos stories sabe um pouco sobre os probleminhas hormonais que passei por tirar o anticoncepcional 💊 da minha vida.. 
Alguns dos sintomas foi a queda capilar e para preservar um pouco dos fios que ainda tinham, tive que cortar 💇🏾‍♀️ curtinho.

Depois de alguns meses meu cabelo mudou completamente a fibra, e a quantidade de frizz não me deixava usa-lo solto, me incomodavam muito. Fiquei com a autoestima lá embaixo.. até conhecer a @gabihairmakeup_ do @sejabardot, eu estava em Vitória e marquei com ela de fazer uma hidratação, ozonioterapira e lá no salão ela me apresentou a escova orgânica com tanino (sem formol). 

Adoooorei o resultado, tirou completamente o frizz, alinhou os meus fios sem tirar o movimento do meu cabelo! Aliado a uma vitamina, meu cabelo cresceu bastante! (Mostrei nos stories)

Voltei a usar meu cabelo solto e bagunçado do jeito que eu gosto. 🌸👙💦🐚

Fiz a escova em setembro, ela sai com o tempo, os frizz ainda não voltaram. Minha experiência foi bemmmm positiva! E com certeza quando voltar em Vix vou passar na @sejabardot 💜💆🏽‍♀️✨. #hair #gopro #goprobr #goprogirl #dicadafepa

caption:
Mirante da Janela, muuuuito amor por esse lugar ✨💚🏞🧗🏽‍♀️. Como eu disse no post anterior, fizemos o Vale da Lua pela manhã e em seguida Mirante da Janela e Abismo. 

A trilha pro Mirante tem em torno de 7km no total e é considerada média/difícil. Foi a trilha que eu mais curti, o visu é lindo! 🥾🏔💦 

As rochas no alto da montanha formam uma janela, por isso o nome. A vista para uma queda d’água de 120 metros é de impressionar. 

Lá você encontra um deck de madeira para contemplar a vista, descansar um pouco e voltar. No retorno parem no Abismo para tomar um banho de cachu e continuar a trilha! 

Coloquem no roteiro porque vale a pena! Valor da entrada: 20,00.

caption:
Um dos lugares que eu mais tinha curiosidade de conhecer na Chapada dos Veadeiros, Vale da Lua 🌒. 

Está localizada a 35km de Alto Paraíso, as formações rochosas milenares lembram a “superfície lunar”. Difícil não se encantar com as rochas lapidadas pela água do Rio São Miguel. 

Além das formações, conseguimos mergulhar e é uma delícia! (mostrei mais nos stories, já está nos destaques). 

Nós a fizemos pela manhã e a tarde conseguimos conciliar com outro passeio (Mirante da Janela e Abismo). 

A trilha é leve e a taxa para entrar é de R$ 20,00. 

𖦹 Guia e Fotos: @luamgabriel

caption:
This week, I was gifted parchment paper and a dutch oven from @kana.goods.  Their products are functional, yet sustainable.

Their parchment paper is made from wood pulp and is completely compostable and biodegradable. I plan on using it with my springform cake pans for easy clean up. Anyone have a birthday coming up? 😉

The dutch oven is made from high quality cast iron and I love the crisp white it adds to my kitchen. I've already used it a few times to cook and can tell it will last me a lifetime. Swipe right ➡️ to see what I created for dinner last night. The Dutch oven is linked in my bio! #Ad #GoodsMadeBetter #PeerKana
-
𝙲𝚞𝚛𝚛𝚒𝚎𝚍 𝚂𝚑𝚛𝚒𝚖𝚙 𝚁𝚒𝚜𝚘𝚝𝚝𝚘 
8 cups chicken stock
2 tbsp olive oil
2 onions, chopped
3 garlic cloves, chopped
3 cups arborio rice
1 tbsp curry powder
Grated zest of 1 lime
Juice of 1 lime
2/3 cup coconut milk
1 lb shrimp, peeled
1/4 cup basil leaves
1 tbsp chopped cilantro
Ground black pepper
Green onions, chopped
[1] In a large stock pot, bring stock to a boil and maintain at a simmer.
[2] Heat your dutch oven over medium-low heat. Add in your olive oil. Saute the onions and garlic until soft (3-4 min). Add in your curry powder and rice and mix well. Mix in lime zest and lime juice.
[3] Ladle in 1/2 cup of the chicken stock into your rice mixture until fully absorbed. Repeat this process until you use up the chicken stock. (~20 min)
[4] Add in shrimp and coconut milk. Mix well to make sure the coconut milk is absorbed. Add in basil and cilantro. Remove from heat and let sit for 5 min.
[5] Top with black pepper to taste and green onions as garnish.
-

caption:
Did everyone know that firm/extra firm tofu should be pressed? Apparently my family knew and no one told me 😂 My mom strained hers overnight in the fridge and my sister built a pressing contraption out of pots and pans (mind you, it would need to sit like that for hours). Luckily, I didn’t need to experiment with that since @tofu.bud came along and gifted me this tofu press. All you have to do is place the tofu in between the plastic strainer pieces and turn the spring to lock it in place. It only takes 15 min to drain the tofu block. #gifted #tofubud #tofupress
-
What are the benefits of pressing tofu? It squeezes out the excess water from the container and allows the tofu to absorb all the flavors you’re working with! It’ll also allow to enjoy its true texture.
-
I’m also partnering up with them for a giveaway 🥳 Follow these rules for your chance to win your own tofu press:
1️⃣ Follow me (@_foodiewithabooty) and @tofu.bud
2️⃣ Tag 3 of your tofu loving friends in the comments
3️⃣ {optional} Share this post to your story for an extra entry and tag us in it.
Giveaway closes Wednesday, 11/18, and is open to US residents only.
OR you can shop directly on their website. The link is in my bio and BOOTY10 will get you 10% off.
-
Pictured here: Air-fried tofu cubes (recipe from Tofu Bud, but modified a bit)
•1 block firm tofu
•1 tbsp sesame oil
•1 tsp soy sauce
•1/4 tsp garlic powder
•1/4 tsp pure maple syrup
•1/4 tsp rice wine vinegar
•2 tsp cornstarch
Mix in ingredients and toss in the air fryer at 325F for 15 min, or until golden.

caption:
It’s not lost on me that dressing up isn’t a priority anymore.

I mean I’ve spent the majority of the week in sweats attempting to muster up enough energy to unload the dishwasher because EVERYTHING seems like a burden. It’s a weird time.

But there are moments when inspiration hits. And I remember what putting an outfit together feels like.

I remember the confidence that comes from that effort.

Yesterday I put on real denim and my whole day was good. Like suspiciously good. I’m not saying that there’s a correlation, but I’m not saying there isn’t 😅

I guess what I’m really saying, is whatever dressing up looks like for you right now, do it. Even just do it once this week. See what it does for you.

Put on a an outfit that excites you even if it’s just to roll out to the mailbox.

PS. Yes, that is a silk camo shirt from Denver’s own @mamcoutureboutique with the @shopdemir black shed bomber jacket.

They sparked my moment of inspiration.

Are you in need of inspiration ❓Save this and let’s talk ideas 👇🏻

caption:
❓What if masculinity wasn’t even a part of the self care conversation❓

Imagine going to the store and picking up the skin and self care products you needed AND wanted without feeling like “less of a man.” 🤯🤯

You wouldn’t need to worry who saw you in the skincare aisle or think of the excuse you have to make up when the cashier sees what you bought.

We’re inching our way there. @stryx_official is in select @cvspharmacy locations and you can pick it up in the men’s grooming and self care aisles.

And you know what❓I was actually stoked to see it in low quantities at the locations I visited for this shoot. That means more guys are actually taking care of their skin and trying some products to build their confidence.

Since trying it for the first time last year, I basically use the concealer pen anytime I’m on camera aaaaaaand I know maybe it’s not as big of a deal as wearing a dress on a cover of a magazine, but the idea is the same.

YOUR MASCULINITY IS NOT COMPROMISED BY YOUR SKIN ROUTINE OR WHAT YOU WEAR.

It’s the small steps to get to that kind of thinking that I’m glad to see happening. @stryx_official is a part of it and I’m stoked to be as well.

You can check out a CVS location carrying Stryx in my stories❗️

📸: @r0melle

caption:
#ad I keep forgetting that tomorrow is Thanksgiving.

A part of me knows it’s going to be a tough day with the usual traditions out the window and dinner looking something more like this ☝🏻☝🏻

I’ve personally struggled with being alone throughout most of social distancing and quarantine and I’ve sort of pushed the holidays out of my mind to lessen that sting.

BUT I do appreciate @sapporobeerusa sending over Sapporo Premium. It feels like they understand the importance of tradition being the oldest brand of beer in Japan and are spreading some of their own tradition through Sapporo Premium. #Sapporo

I appreciate their help in keeping at least one tradition alive of sharing a beer with my family (even if it’s over zoom).

Makes me realize how grateful I am for even small real interactions with friends and family.

caption:
You know I often forget that I’m still at the beginning of my creative journey.

Whether it’s because of comparison or my own self motivation, one thought that continues to live rent free in my head is that I should be further ahead of where I am.

Like, yea of course we all want that. We want to be at the party instead of just trying to get invite.

But then I see my role models on here tell their stories. Specifically how it’s taken them 5 years, 10 years, etc. to really master their craft.

And it puts me in my place a little bit. Like, so much has happened in the last 3 years (let a lone the last 10 months). From weekend hobby to full time career. Continuing to just focus on skipping ahead is really unproductive.

If you’re a creative, if you’re just stepping into your own style and confidence, or if you’re just a person... you’re on your own journey and you’re on your own time.

You’ll get where you need to be. Promise.

Tell me if you’ve been feeling this same way and what you’re end goal is.

caption:
Love what you do and you’ll never work a day in your life.. right❓

Truth is you’ll probably work harder, stress harder and enjoy it harder (❓🧐)

If you’re a creator hunting growth, sponsored deals, and better and better content then chances are it’s gonna feel like work.

Inevitably work gets tiring and can suck the fun out of what you were originally passionate about.

Even when you’re passion becomes so much as a side hustle, you need to keep that balance.

I’m needing it right now. It’s felt like a lot of my creation has become work. Which is great but also makes it feel less creative in a sense and also turned into disassociation from what I create.

So here’s what I’m doing:

1. Block time to create organic content that is born out of pure creativity.

2. Create things just for me. Meaning I don’t have to share it if I don’t want to.

3. Reclaim the creative power over my platform. This might sound weird, but what I mean is that I’m being more strategic and selective for sponsored content I choose and restructuring deals and freelancing more to bring some relief to what “has” to get posted.

Drop a 🦐in the comments if these make sense, especially that last one.

Remember that balance is key in any work-life setting.

caption:
I’ve got the most trust issues when I’m just trying to trust the process.

Anyone else❓

I looked at my calendar last night to check on what I had scheduled today. 3 things: shoot a little content, review client profiles, and plan a blog. And I actually felt panicked.

Not because it was too much, but because I felt like the day was light. So I immediately added some other planning time for the rest of the month as well as editing time. The guilt for a relaxed weekend rushed in.

Like dang❗️Can I get a minute from the guilt induced anxiety❓

And then it hit me. Trusting that a couple items in a day is the right process is a learning curve. And trying to do more in one day is just me trying to gain control of that process.

Sometimes you can’t.

Have you been feeling this too❓I feel like right now we’re all just in a position of trusting things will work out and grappling with a lack of control.

caption:
What does it take to make 💰💰on social media❓

When I first started, I thought the path was to 📈 followers because that lead to the big bucks. But that’s not entirely true.

Yes, the size of your audience can help, but that number DOES NOT DEFINE YOUR SUCCESS, does not define your revenue, and does not define your skill.

There are creators with small, niche audiences that are crushing more than macroinfluencers.

When I talk to new creators or clients, that’s our first discussion. Once you get past the idea that vanity and popularity equal success, you can actually get some work done here.

So what do you need to start earning❓Here’s what I’ve learned:

1. Flexibility. If you’re passionate, find multiple ways to sell your content and your brand. Sponsored content, freelancing, consulting.

2. Consistency. If you give up before your spinning wheels catch, then of course it won’t happen.

3. Education mindset. Everything changes so quickly, so if you’re not willing to keep learning and getting better, then you’re just doing yourself a disservice. Stay ahead of the game so you can sell what you do.

4. Community. Maybe not directly linked, but finding people who make you feel less crazy because they get it AND build you up when you have that idea or ask for more is 🔑

I’m doubling down and going to be sharing more of what I’ve learned these last few years. Content collab course coming soon along with more yt videos on what you need to know weekly. PLUS, I’m giving tips daily on tiktok, so if you’re over there come find me!

I want to give you the help I felt like I needed when I was starting.

📸: @threadability

caption:
They said Holidays are the hardest when you loss someone so close to you and sad to say they are right. It’s been barely 5months since Mommy became an angel.🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼 
Some days are definitely harder than others.😢

Yesterday, I tried to keep myself busy by cleaning, decorating, cooking —  prepping for our Thanksgiving dinner but I couldn’t hide it.😞 I miss Mommy and shed so much tears.😢 I’m praying for strength, especially for Daddy for the next holidays. If you are in the same situation, I am praying for you.🙏🏼. Let’s all pray for each other for strength and healing. May our hearts be completely healed and be at peace.🙏🏼🥰♥️

I hope you all had a great Thanksgiving with your family and friends.
HAPPY THANKSGIVING FROM MY FAMILY TO YOURS!🍁🍽♥️
If you are going out for #BlackFriday shopping today, please be extra careful. #maskup and observe proper hand hygiene.

📸December 2019
Our last Christmas with Mommy. It was God’s gift that my brother was able to spend the holidays with us last year.🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

caption:
We just got the word!!! We will see my husband late this month!!!♥️🙏🏼👨‍👩‍👦 
Crossing my fingers and praying hard that nothing will change because you know, things always change in the military.🤞🏼🙏🏼

On the other hand, everyday grateful for all the brave men and women who are serving our country and sacrificing their time which they could have spend it with their family and loved ones. They serve, left their family, friends, loved ones behind and have all the hopes of coming back home. Also, to all the ones who are left behind, thank you so much for all your support.

My husband hasn’t been deployed yet but they go off shore a lot. We are also not close to where he is stationed so we only see each other if we have longer days off. Yes, it’s hard but we have to make it through. This pandemic also made it worse. We only saw him 3x this year which we used to try to see him every other month.😞 Anyway, as long as he’s safe. That’s all that matters to us.🥰👨‍👩‍👦🙏🏼

To everyone who served and everyone that didn’t make it back home safely, your service will never be forgotten. 🤍🇺🇸 THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR YOUR SERVICE!
Happy Veterans Day!
#HappyVeteransDay

caption:
Hhhmmmm... I don’t even know where to start.
First of, THIS IS NOT A PREGNANCY ANNOUNCEMENT — I WISH IT WAS THOUGH😢🙏🏼

Late June, my Mom passed away from Metastatic Breast Cancer which she fought for 10years.😢 I was heartbroken, still heartbroken.💔😭 We all are. 

Two weeks later, I found out I was pregnant. My heart was pounding, hands were shaking, tears were falling and just had so much emotions in me. Sooo happy and sad at the same time. Happy because God finally answered our prayers but sad because Mommy won’t be able to meet another grand baby.😢
Mommy whispered to God how much we wanted another baby...

That didn’t last long. I had the slightest spotting just two weeks after I found out I was pregnant. It wasn’t even bright red, just a pink tinged. I tried to stay positive but already had that bad feeling. I saw my OB early at 6weeks  and she only saw a sac, so she ordered a blood work to check my HCG levels and it was about 33,000+ which is good.🙏🏼 So she did another ultrasound and saw a yolk sac and a tiny embryo with no cardiac activity. It was early so we were trying to stay positive and do another ultrasound the following week. I tell you, I spent so much time searching and watching for videos/stories with similar experience that had a positive outcome. At least just to give myself hope but there wasn’t much. Despite that, I continued to pray and so did  family and close friends. I can see that my OB was also trying to stay positive for me since she knew my Mom just passed. She wanted to give me some good news... Fast forward after I had 4 transvaginal and 1 abdominal ultrasound, my OB confirmed that I had a miscarriage. She gave me an option if I want to wait, take a medication or have a D&C(Dilation & curettage). I bawled😭 I just don’t know what to do and why this is all happening. My Mom was an OB-Gyn and she would have been the perfect person to ask.😭😭😭
My heart didn’t even had time to heal and now it’s shattered again.😢
 
...to be continued in comments. ⬇️⬇️⬇️

caption:
The day after Thanksgiving was filled with excitement and wonder for our little boys. After meeting Santa, the boys and I attended the opening night of @tanakafarms Hikari, A Festival of Lights, with the @ocmommybloggertribe 

Having been there only a month before, for their Halloween ride, it was a pleasure to see how Tanaka Farms dressed up for the holidays, as we drove through the festive farm. 

We even got to catch up with a few of our OC Mommy Blogger Tribe families, who had the same time a lot as us. This is always a huge treat for me and the boys, because we get to see our friends (and run through the Christmas tree lot with them 🤪)

caption:
I couldn’t stop laughing yesterday, because the boys did NOT want to go home after we visited the @3darmuseum 
It’s located on the 3rd Street Promenade, so they asked me to take them out to lunch and then wanted to walk around and do some shopping. 
Honestly, I couldn’t get over their shopping discussions. 
For the first time in their lives, I stood back and let them pick and choose what they wanted (the sales were pretty incredible), and it was absolutely adorable. 
I’m just so happy for this week-long break from Distance Learning and Homeschooling.  We are all so excited to get out of the house and do a little exploring. 
I know everything is starting to shut down again, and I have my concerns. At the same time, it feels like we’re finally starting to spread our wings a little and I want to allow that because it’s so obviously necessary for the kids and me.  Grateful for the lovely day out!

caption:
It was a strange morning, getting myself and the boys ready to actually go somewhere.  I kept thinking we were going on another drive thru experience, but we were actually headed to a real indoor pop up museum. It’s been a while!

I have to say, as much as I love wearing jammies and experiencing things from the comfort of my car, nothing, and I mean NOTHING, compares to actually walking inside of a museum and exploring. 
Especially, when it’s safely done!

We were invited to visit the @3darmuseum in Santa Monica via @themommybloggertribe and are absolutely grateful for the experience. 

We arrived at our scheduled visit time and were greeted by the lovely staff and manager. Our temperatures were taken and I was kindly instructed to log on to their WiFi and download the app which turns every installation into a really awesome moving image. 

The space is large and there were only two other people scheduled at our visit time.  We didn’t see the other guests after the checkin process, so it felt like we had the place to ourselves. 

Friends, it was FUN! I have to say, I was a little hesitant initially, because my boys can’t stand how many pictures I take of them, but with the app and the amazing videos I was taking of them slaying dragons, playing football, and jumping volcanos, they couldn’t wait to get to the next instillation.

Timid at first, my little ones opened up and really had a great time. 

This is not something you want to miss 💕

caption:

caption:
Sometimes I stop to think how lucky we are to live in Los Angeles, were so much is in close proximity. 

My father lives about an hour away, and has snow at his house.  We could have been playing in the snow this weekend, but decided we preferred a beachier vibe, an island vibe, and 45 minutes later we were on Catalina Island. 
I mean, who else gets to do that? 

Tomorrow we might decide we want to hike the dessert, Joshua Tree is less than two hours away... or take my dad up on that snowy getaway. I seriously love where we live!

caption:
[#ad] Our boys are still playing with their @justplayproducts PJ Masks Transforming 2 in 1 Mobile HQ months later. I’d say that’s a huge win!

The kiddos were blown away by the sheer size of this amazing and fun transformer, when we originally got it for them a few months ago. They loved that they had the ability to open and close this HUGE playset, and immediately got out all of their PJ Masks vehicles and characters. They had a great time playing out scenes from the show.
Months later, this enormous toy (that folds up small) is the playing hub for lots of other games. It has been an RV for their action figure’s camping trips, a an army base, a surveillance van, and most recently, a stage for their wrestling toys... oh and an apartment building. 
I love all of the imaginative ways the boys are using this toy. If it sparks imagination, I’m on board. 

This would make a lovely holiday gift for any child! 

We ordered our @pjmasks Transforming 2 in 1 Mobile HQ on @amazon (link in bio)

You can also find this fun toy at @target and @walmart

caption:
Yesterday was #MidAutumnFestival and it brought out all the feels... it was my first time celebrating without my grandmother. 💔 My 娜娜 (“nana” for paternal grandmother) was a smart, independent, kind and classy lady who always taught me that I could do and be anything that I put my heart and mind to. She lived a full life which, in many ways, was ahead of her time:
⭐️ Went to college and graduated with an English degree. 👩🏻‍🎓
⭐️ Was an English teacher in Shanghai. 📝
⭐️ Both her children immigrated here to the US, which was her dream for them. 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦
⭐️ Traveled all around the world with my grandfather when he worked at Coca-cola. 🌏
⭐️ Loved and was loved by her family. ❤️
I only wish I could’ve been by her side during her final moments. 😔 #FlashbackFriday #RIP

caption:
#GoProHERO9 🔥
WEEKEND MOOD💛
感謝 @gopro @goprotw 的邀請讓我參與今年的 #GoProCreatorSummit 

2020因為疫情的關係影響

caption: Ik werd altijd bewonderd voor het lef dat ik getoond had op 20-jarige leeftijd om te gaan voor mijn dromen. Gewoon doen wat mijn hart me vertelde. Stoppen met studeren, alleen gaan wonen, full-time beginnen werken in mijn eigen zaak. Dat heeft me altijd getypeerd de jaren nadien. Het werd deel van mijn identiteit. Laurentine, de durf-al. Laurentine zonder angst. Laurentine die zich overal gewoon in smijt. Armen open, ogen toe. Je kan je voorstellen hoe pijnlijk en frustrerend het was om dat deel van mezelf plots kwijt te zijn. Ik heb twee jaar gezocht en voel nu dat ze er terug is. Ik sta in mijn kracht omdat ik het idee los liet dat het perfect moet zijn. Dat ik nu al exact moet weten waar ik ga landen. Dat ik niet goed genoeg ben om te doen waar ik toe voorbestemd ben. Wat ik nu doe ligt zoveel dichter bij mijn ziel dan ‘kleren verkopen’ en het is daarom ook veel enger om daarin te ondernemen. Angst is een slechte raadgever. Beginnen moeten we altijd ergens. Natuurlijk zijn er mensen die meer opgeleid zijn. Natuurlijk zijn er mensen die al ongeveer doen wat jij wil doen. But no-one is you. And that is your power. ✨ quote by @dangerouswco
comments: ❤️; 👏🙌👏; Laurentine ❤️ Ik bewonder je natuurlijk voor je ondernemerszin, maar nog het meest voor je persoonlijke groei. En dat wij daar nu van mogen leren is 😍😍😍; Woorden die ik zocht & door u vond. Amai, Merci 💛;

caption: Na een redelijk traumatische ervaring die voort kwam uit een Tinder-match, had ik er ff genoeg van. Sowieso vind ik al jaren weinig aan die app. Ik zit er nooit meer dan 2 weken op om dan weer te verwijderen voor maanden. Tinder roept bij mijn vriendinnen die vaker daten wel meer frustraties op. Vorige week hoorde ik een spannend verhaal van de ene vriendin en een romantisch van een andere. Ik dacht “godverdomme, ik kan ook nog wel eens wat “thrills” gebruiken.” Onze beste vriend C & de getroffen maatregelen maakt het allemaal nogal eentonig, hé? Hoewel ik niet te klagen heb; ik doe elke dag met veel passie wat ik graag doe, ik kan super goed alleen zijn en voel me mega happy. Ook dat “verlangen naar een man” duurt vaak niet langer dan een avond. Maar goed, los daarvan. Tinder. Je downloadt dat. Zet er een paar leuke foto’s op. Ik had deze ook genomen want ja, happy vibes, eentje met zonnebril mocht ook wel, vriendin dabei, feestje (= kijk, ik ben fun)... Je hoort dan eigenlijk iets in je “bio” te schrijven maar eerlijk, daar begin ik zelfs niet aan. How the fuck moet ik waar ik voor sta en wie ik ben daarin samenvatten? Je kan ook gaan voor een gevat zinnetje ofzo maar als ze dat dan verkeerd interpreteren? Er is geen context. Je ziet enkel foto’s. En dan ga je dus swipen. Oh. Oh man. Wat je allemaal tegenkomt. Het blijft me verbazen. Nu ja, er moet voor ieder wat wils zijn zeker? En op ieder potje zou blijkbaar een dekseltje passen. Een minimaal aantal keer swipe ik rechts. Oh, een match. Leuk. Komt er ofwel niets uit hun digitale mond ofwel zeggen ze iets dat me meteen mateloos irriteert. Of ze zijn lief, tof en enthousiast en toch denk ik “nahhh”. Hoe oppervlakkig is het ook eigenlijk om alleen op je uiterlijk beoordeeld te worden en omgekeerd? Ik denk dat veel potjes en dekseltjes elkaar daarom mislopen op zo’n app. Geef mij maar de toevallige ontmoeting (moeilijk these days haha). Maar kijk, het zal vast en zeker aan mij liggen. Of aan het feit dat ik niet “op zoek” ben. Want dan hoor ik eigenlijk niet erop te zitten. Hoe dan ook heb ik de app liever niet op mijn gsm. Ik heb er deze week een uur van mijn leven aan verloren. 🤷🏻‍♀️ Who feels me?
comments: Ik had dit gevoel ook, ging toen Tinder verwijderen en nooit meer installeren, checkte toch mn matches nog eens voor de ‘zekerheid’ en zag toen iemand waarvan ik dacht huh waarom heb ik geen berichtje gestuurd.. nu bijna 2 jaar samen met die jongen 😂 funny how that works. Maar ik snap je verhaal wel helemaal!; 🙋🏻‍♀️ volledig eens met jou!; @lien_muyldermans daarom doe ik het dus niet... Sorry not sorry... 😘😘; 'Ofwel zeggen ze iets dat me meteen mateloos irriteert' 🙋‍♀️ i feel ya 😂;

caption: Het is niet goed gesteld met het mentaal welzijn van jongeren. 🥺 @stadsintniklaas deed een enquête en daaruit bleek ze zich vaak alleen voelen, de meesten zien de examenperiode niet zitten en 5% kan bij niemand terecht met hun problemen. 🌧 Ik zoom-de (is dat nu een werkwoord of niet?) heel de week met klassen van het 5e en 6e middelbaar om hen een beetje moed in te spreken, selfcare tips te geven en de verschillende instanties waar ze terecht kunnen toe te lichten. 🙏 @baasinsintniklaas richtte hier speciaal een nieuw initiatief voor op: Jong Wild Goud. Waar dit “hoe is ’t?” project het eerste van was. Dit is geen ad maar iets wat ik zelf wil delen. ✌️Omdat de jongeren zich niet gehoord voelen. Er wordt weinig rekening gehouden met waar zij nu door moeten. Wat zij voelen. Wat zij denken. In het Tejohuis kunnen ze terecht voor 10 gratis & anonieme pyschologische begeleidingssessies. Ik hoop oprecht dat ze mijn tips gaan toepassen & daar langs gaan. De belangrijkste boodschap die ik meegegeven heb is dat ze niet alleen zijn. En dat naar een psycholoog gaan helemaal niets is om u voor te schamen. Dat ik het al doe van toen ik 16 was. Dat zou helemaal geen taboe mogen zijn. 🌼 Blijf aan mensen vragen hoe het écht met hun gaat. Het is nu nòg belangrijker dan ooit. ❤️ Heel dankbaar dat ik deel mocht uit maken van dit project! ✨
comments: This girl was on fire! 🔥 Zo leuk om met jou te werken!; ❤️; Geweldig project 👊; 😍😍;

caption: “You are a thriving, intricate, complex, sangria mix of your own stories and your own paint. Fuck off anything that takes you away from how you move through the world, and lean into any kind of sun, that brings you back to your own God damn rebellion. The holy gray of art is knowing who you are and painting it outwards. And you will only find that, if you start looking into the X-marked treasure trove of your own soul.” 📸 @jesuisirmy #IrmyPhotography #quotebyBrookeSolis

Exact dit. Tijd om het tij te keren. Tijd om te stoppen met over-werken te idealiseren. Ook ik heb mezelf moeten ontdoen van het aangeleerde non-stop bezig zijn waar ik mee ben opgegroeid. Hard werken was het minimum. Tijd voor jezelf nemen onbestaande. Maar er is helemaal niks ‘cool’ aan uzelf kapot werken en gaan tot je niet meer kan. Want als je écht niet meer kan, gaat het licht uit. Ik kan je vertellen dat dat niet fijn is. En de weg terug is langzaam. Leerrijk, dat wel. Maar voor geen geld van de wereld wil ik nog terug naar de race waar ik in zat en ik verzet er me nu met elke vezel in mijn lichaam tegen. Het is namelijk geen race en in the end winnen we alleen als we kunnen zeggen dat we gelééfd hebben, toch? 🙏

Dus laten we stoppen met applaudisseren voor mensen die opscheppen over een 80-uren werkweek. Laten we juichen als iemand op tijd rust neemt voor zichzelf. 👏

Quote van @katyleeson ✨

caption: “Our transformation is not always loud or arrow fast. Sometimes - it’s years later, you’re standing there, your jaw softens and you realize you’re no longer the same as when you first walked in. Where you were once closed, you have now let yourself slowly fold open. Where you were once hardened, you have now become weathered silk and see-through. It is okay to be here. It is okay not to rush through and destroy your middle - the place where you reach for the future just before you shed yourself of the past. Each valley holds rich value. Each in-between gifts you the resilience to great what’s next” ✨ pics by @jesuisirmy #enjoythejourney #thatislife #textwrittenbydanielledoby #irmyphotography #tb

caption:
Hetgeen wat zich nu manifesteert is niet iets wat er plots was. Al meer dan 2 jaar had ik het @_glowcommunity_ idee en toch startte ik niet. Degene die me up-close volgen weten dat dit gepaard ging met soms zware highs maar vaak ook enorme lows. Zoals het leven, natuurlijk. Maar nog meer met - naar mijn gevoel - “een beetje aanmodderen”. Zingeving ontbrak. “Wat ben ik eigenlijk aan het doen met mijn leven?!” Ik had de vrijheid die ik altijd al wou en het toch gaf het me geen voldoening. Ik wist wat ik wou en ook wat ik daarvoor moest doen en ondernam geen actie. Dat FRUSTREERDE (met hoofdletters ja) me ELKE FUCKING DAG. Ondertussen zag ik bij andere mensen wel zaadjes geplant worden. Soms zaadjes die een mini-beetje leken op het plantje dat ik wou. Ook dat was lastig. Ik probeerde vast te houden aan “enjoy the journey, enjoy the journey” omdat ik wist dat ik op een dag terug ging kijken en snappen waarom het allemaal zo moest gebeuren. Dat was niet makkelijk. Dat was heel, heel, heel moeilijk. En toch bleef ik trouw aan mezelf. Ik plooide niet voor wat er van mij verwacht werd door de maatschappij. I sat with myself. Ik leerde. Ik groeide. Non-stop. De momenten dat je vast zit zijn de grootste leermomenten. Als ik 2 jaar geleden met mijn project gestart was, had het nooit dezelfde waarde gehad als nu. Looking back; the dots connect, always. En het was elke traan en frustratie waard. Ik dacht dat ik stil stond maar ik vloog. Richting dit moment. READY TO GLOW ✨ #issamood 

And also: get yourself friends that support you like this 😭❤️ @soulsoup.be
comments: ❤️❤️; Rockin it hun 💪🏻💥; Zo mooi en zo herkenbaar!🙌🏼; ♥️;

caption:
Ik stak vroeger nooit kaarsen aan. Ik heb eens een half jaar geen kleerkast gehad; in mijn living stonden rekken. Ik leefde vaak in een rommeltje. Ik was enkel thuis om te slapen. Binnen - buiten. Nooit zat ik even neer. Altijd aan het werk, weg of onderwege. Maakte daarom van mijn huis geen thuis. Stopte geen moeite in decoreren of het gezellig maken. 

Ik zat hier net in mijn zetel te kijken naar het kaarslicht dat danst en kreeg kippenvel. Een rust viel over mij en de ‘zorgeloosheid’ die ik altijd wou - is er. Wat een verschil toch met vroeger. Mijn huis is opgeruimd. Ik heb geen overbodige rommel meer, nergens. I minimalisted the shit out of all the stuff I had, haha. Dat geeft zoveel clarity en ruimte (letterlijk maar ook in je hoofd). En ik ben zelfs van plan een kast in het roos te schilderen en mijn eetruimte waar ik nooit fan van was toch een kans te geven. Maandag komt er een kuisvrouw, vanaf nu elke 2 weken. Want dat verdien ik. 

Door mezelf graag te (leren) zien, tijd te nemen om stil te staan & léven op nummer 1 te zetten is er zo veel veranderd. 

✨ Foto van Pinterest tijdens mijn inspo-zoektocht

Hoe is dit bij jullie? Ik ben wel benieuwd 🙏

caption:
Liefste lichaam,

Bedankt dat je steeds voor mij bleef zorgen, ook al had ik het niet altijd makkelijk om jou te aanvaarden. Je bleef mij dragen. Tijdens de dagen dat ik je als 13-jarige enkel crackers en perziken gunde. Tijdens de dagen dat jij mijn middel van controle was. Tijdens de avonden dat alles wat ik ‘te veel at’, ook weer uit jou moest. Bedankt om er zelfs dan nog te blijven zijn voor mij. We heelden, herstelden en groeiden samen. Wat een opluchting moet dat voor jou zijn geweest. En voor mij, want ik ontdekte dat jij niet tegen mij werkt, maar samen met mij. Bedankt om mij te leren inzien wanneer ik rust moet nemen. Vandaag luister ik meer dan ooit naar jou. Bedankt om mij door trauma te loodsen. Je werkt écht op miraculeuze wijze. Bedankt om mij telkens de signalen te sturen die ik nodig heb. Samen vinden wij altijd een oplossing. Bedankt voor de tranen die je laat vloeien wanneer ik daar nood aan heb. Bedankt voor mijn ongelooflijk brede lach, ondanks mijn dunne lippen. Bedankt voor alles wat mij ‘mij’ maakt. Bedankt voor alles wat ik dankzij jou kan doen. Bedankt om mij te beschermen. Bedankt voor de kleine en grote wonderen die ik samen met jou beleef. Bedankt. Vandaag zijn we samen sterker dan ooit want… ik aanvaard je. Ik zorg voor je. Ik heb je lief. Ik koester je. Ik hou van je.

Laurentine

@nina_hln vroeg me een liefdesbrief aan mijn lijf te schrijven. Ik daag jullie uit het ook te doen 💌

caption: Drie weken geleden werd mijn idee om een webinar te geven concreet. Ik vroeg jullie welk onderwerp interessant zou zijn. Mijn ‘Glow Morning Routine’ kwam vaak naar voor. Zonder al te veel nadenken (dat had ik meer dan 2 jaar gedaan) zorgde ik ervoor dat mensen zich konden inschrijven. Het doel was 50 kijkers. Twee weken later zat ik voor mijn computer tegen jullie te lallen. Volledig mezelf, helemaal in mijn nopjes. Zonder blad voor de mond. Twee uur praten over iets waar ik super enthousiast over ben. Over tools en lessen die mijn leven veranderden en nu - blijkbaar - dat van jullie. Vandaag, een week nadien, hebben al meer dan 500 (!!!) mensen het webinar bekeken. Ik kan het nog steeds niet bevatten. De energie in de groep was ongelooflijk. Hetgeen waar ik van droomde - een échte community opbouwen met @_glowcommunity_ - was plots geboren. Ineens was het daar. “Meer échte impact” was wat ik wou met mijn nieuw bedrijf. Ook dat werd realiteit. Ik heb gehuild, geroepen, gedanst en op & neer gesprongen toen ik mijn laptop dicht klapte. Ik was zo hyped dat ik een paar uur later nog niet lag te slapen. Een hele week al heb ik nagenoten. Wat een magisch medium is dit toch. Ik ben dankbaar, zo zo zo dankbaar. Jullie doen me in mezelf geloven. Jullie geven mij vleugels. Jullie geven mij kracht. CHEERS TO THAT ✨ [swipe voor recensies 🙏 eigen stoef stinkt maar als een ander iets zegt, is het wel OK, toch?]
comments: 🙏🙏🙏; Zo geweldig 👏🏻❤️; En die impact blijft niet bij die reeds 500 kijkers! Ik heb ondertussen mijn ouders en een aantal vrienden hierover verteld, om ook hen dat duwtje in de rug te geven 😊 Ik voel me oprecht gelukkiger dan ik sinds de eerste lockdown tot voor het webinar heb gevoeld! Dankje ❤️; Keep on glowing you sparkle of sunshine 💛💛💛;

caption:
In de voorbereiding van mijn webinar kwam ik weer op de volgende tekst uit. De boodschap is zo fucking sterk:
“Our deepest fear is not that we are inadequate. Our deepest fear is that we are powerful beyond measure. It is our light, not our darkness, that most frightens us. Your playing small does not serve the world. There is nothing enlightened about shrinking so that other people won't feel insecure around you. We are all meant to shine as children do. It's not just in some of us; it is in everyone. And as we let our own lights shine, we unconsciously give other people permission to do the same. As we are liberated from our own fear, our presence automatically liberates others.” - Marianne Williamson ✨

caption:

caption: Het is mentaal zwaar voor velen. Ik merk het in de DM’s die ik krijg. Ik merk het aan vrienden. Ik merk het hier bij mensen die ik volg op social media. De ontelbare redenen waarom het zwaar is, daar hebben we weinig aan. Waar we wel iets aan hebben, is elkaar. Praat met elkaar. Vraag uw vrienden hoe het met ze gaat. Stuur kaartjes. Wees je eigen beste vriend. Zoek naar het moois in elke dag. Check het nieuws niet. Ga de natuur in. Zet uw favoriet liedje op en dans. Laat uw gevoelens toe en de tranen rollen; je hoeft niet elke dag sterk te zijn. Mediteer of doe een poging tot; niemand is pro in iets wat hij voor de eerste keer doet. Bestel verf en schilder. Leg een puzzel. Beperk uw social media gebruik. Zoek iets om je op te focussen; een doel, een nieuwe passie, een project, iets wat je wil bijleren. Lees een roman of leer uit een selfhelpbook. Daag jezelf uit en doorbreek patronen, leer jezelf een nieuwe gewoonte aan. De afleiding is nog nooit zo minimaal geweest. Er is veel wat niet kan maar er is ook nog veel wat wel kan. En like nu niet alleen deze post. Doe het. Sommige dingen zullen oncomfortabel aanvoelen omdat je er nooit eerder tijd voor nam of ‘omdat je gewoon geen zin hebt’. Maar je moet me geloven als ik zeg dat je je achteraf beter gaat voelen. 💛✨
comments: Zo waar! De natuur ingaan, zo rustgevend! En praten met elkaar, zo belangrijk!❤️; ❤️; 😍😍😍; Wat een schattig hondje 😍😍😍🏆;

caption: In een Ted Talk die ik laatst keek, ging een vrouw op zoek naar de oorzaak van waarom mensen in bepaalde gebieden (the blue zone in Sardinië) langer leven. Ik leerde dat niet voeding, beweging of clean air het meeste impact hebben. Wel het day-to day sociaal contact, mensen waarop je kan rekenen & de hechte community waarin mensen leven. Daaraan zie je hoe on-ge-loof-lijk belangrijk het is. Je banden met mensen. Voor je gezondheid. We worden hier nu compleet van ontnomen en dat heeft een impact op ons welzijn. Ik bel sindskort elke dag één vriend(in) op om te vragen hoe het gaat. Hoe check jij in met je vrienden? 💛

caption:
“Niets is toeval.” Ik kan het aantal keren dat ik dat zei de laatste 2 weken, niet meer tellen. 🙈 Ik geloof al jaren in ‘het lot’. Daarom staat er ook ‘Fortune favours the brave’ op mijn hoofd getatoeëerd. En sinds kort een regenboogje op mijn pols, wat heel veel betekenis heeft voor me (leg ik nog eens uit in een andere caption). Dat we vandaag exact op het uur dat er een regenboog was, het strand opwandelden - is volgens mij het universum dat een signaal geeft. 🙏 Iets wat ik diep vanbinnen voel de laatste tijd: “I’m on the right track”. & shit, it feel soooo good. 

Ik stuur regenbogen naar iedereen die het nodig heeft momenteel. 🌈✨ 

Denken jullie dat dingen toevallig gebeuren? Of zijn ze voorbestemd? Hoe ervaar je dit? 💛

(Er zijn geen foute antwoorden trouwens!)

23/10/2013 - 7 jaar geleden volgde ik mijn hart. Blindelings en vol vertrouwen. Een rollercoaster werd het. En wat voor één. Soms kan ik niet geloven dat het allemaal écht gebeurd is. Ik ben dankbaar voor alles. Elke seconde. ✨

In de antroposofische filosofie zeggen ze dat je leven volgens cycli verloopt die 7 jaar duren. Iedere periode is het accent van je ontwikkeling ergens anders op gericht. Ik voel dat ik nu, exact 7 jaar later, een ongelooflijke transformatie doormaak & ik ben zo, zo, zo ongelooflijk klaar voor alles wat gaat komen 🙏

caption: SUCH AN IMPORTANT MESSAGE 👏 En het hoeft niet eens een panic attack te zijn of negatieve gevoelens die je ervaart. Het leven vraagt veel van ons, of beter: wij verwachten veel van onszelf. Alle ballen hoog houden. Mijn grootste struggle & iets waar ik het meeste stress rond ervaar (erg om toe te geven) is het “constant bereikbaar zijn” van deze tijd. Via whatsapp. Instagram DM. Mail. Facebook. Sms. The list is long. Tijdens COF was het het constant bezig zijn dat me daarin belemmerde. Ik racete van hot naar her, was enkel thuis om te slapen. En nu ik meer tijd heb, maak ik andere keuzes. Ik zet mezelf vaker op de eerste plek. Wat betekent dat ik soms gewoon geen mental space heb. Om te antwoorden. Mensen zien me dan wel posten op Instagram (= part of my job) en krijgen daardoor soms verkeerdelijk het gevoel dat ze niet belangrijk genoeg zijn. Breekt mijn hart want dat is uiteraard niet zo. Vaak zie ik zoveel whatsappjes staan dat ik zelfs de moed niet heb om er aan te beginnen. Om nog maar te zwijgen over de DM’s op Instagram. Daar zie ik door de bomen het bos niet meer. Of het is een bericht waar ik “mijn tijd voor wil nemen en met aandacht op wil antwoorden” en die tijd komt maar niet. Het berichtje schuift meer naar onder. And so on. Ik raak nooit bijgebeend. Het is hetgeen waar ik me het het meest schuldig over voel en waar ik toch maar niet in “slaag”, hoe graag ik ook wil. Elke dag waag ik een nieuwe poging. Echt. Oprecht. Want iemand (vriend/volger) kwetsen of hierdoor verliezen is het laatste wat ik wil. Ik voel dat ik wil eindigen met een verontschuldiging maar de boodschap is eigenlijk dat we dat minder zouden moeten doen. Heb je het moeilijk en daarom geen energie om mij te antwoorden? I understand. Heb je een super leuke dag en wil je niet met je gsm bezig zijn waardoor ik later pas antwoord krijg? Both are perfectly fine 🙋🏻‍♀️ PROTECT YOUR PEACE BECAUSE EVERYTHING STARTS THERE ✨

caption:
Today we celebrate Thanksgiving. This year has been so different and felt so weird. Normally on Thanksgiving we would be gathered at our house all 40 or so of our family members around a table sharing laughs and a meal. (Y’all know my family is like the Griswolds it’s always a party) This year we are on the road to the mountains to celebrate Thanksgiving just the 4 of us. If we’ve learned anything this year it’s learning to adjust and roll with the punches. I’m learning to let go of the control because let’s face it, none of us are in control. 
.
I’m thankful for the gift of time this year. We’ve had so much more of it as a family. (And you probably have too) Even though in the early stages of quarantine all there was to look forward to was taking a bike ride or taking a family walk, I’m thankful for that quality time that I normally would have taken for granted. 
.
We’ve taught our kids that it doesn’t really matter where we are on Thanksgiving (on the road, in a hotel, or just sitting at home) as long as we have each other that’s what’s important. I think I’m learning this too. 
.
I also believe this horrible virus has taught many of us how short life really is. Let go of anger. Forgive that person who wronged you. Take the time to tell your loved ones you love them. It’s just not worth holding onto anger or resentment.  Call up your family and tell them you love them today. 
.
.From my family to yours, Happy Thanksgiving. I am very grateful for you all and this wonderful community that I consider a second family. ♥️
comments: Happy Thanksgiving 🦃; Such a weird thanksgiving and year. Hope you and your family had a wonderful Thanksgiving adventure! 🖤🍁🦃🧡; Hope you had an amazing thanksgiving. Beautiful picture 🖤; Collab? DM #vincerewears;

caption: We’ve had so many things thrown against us. We’ve fought through so many obstacles. Someone even told Jason I wasn’t worth marrying because I came from a “broken home” divorced parents. We’ve been through literal hell and back. Miscarriage, broke, living off frozen pizzas or ramen every night, gosh the valleys of life- you name it. But we keep on fighting. Marriage is HARD. We aren’t perfect. Gosh so far from it. When people say we are “goals” that makes me chuckle because we still fight over the most RIDICULOUS things like who gets more honey mustard for the CFA nuggets. 🤣 but gosh darn I love this man and the life we are creating. Marriage is about fighting. Fighting for IT! It’s a choice. It’s good, hard, frustrating, annoying, blissful, and beautiful. 💕 Give me some of your BEST marriage tips! Jason would say don’t ever go to bed angry. I would say choose each other first. Every single day.

it’s easy to be grateful for the good things // read that again 👆🏻
.
.
this year on thanksgiving I am taking a different approach. i’m sitting & reflecting & forcing myself to see the good in a very challenging year. 
.
.
of course I am grateful for my family, friends, health, home. it’s easy for me to see how blessed I am in those areas. but without hard things - there is no growth. so here it is (be gentle with me, this wasn’t easy to write or admit)
.
.
i am grateful for COVID: it brought my family home from overseas for over a month. it showed me what relationships were real + which weren’t. it showed me the value of HEALTH. SAFETY. SECURITY. LOVE. it showed us that so often the people we overlook (cashiers, bus drivers, uber drivers, TEACHERS) are our foundation. 
.
.
I am grateful for the people who didn’t treat me the way I deserved. I learned my worth. It was hard. It hurt. But I learned my breaking point. 
.
.
I am grateful for the people who gave me hard feedback on FITISH. it drove me to do better. to test wear. to demand more of others so I could deliver more to you. 
.

I am grateful for the (sometimes crippling) amount of alone time. before I was traveling 200 days a year + never stopping. I didn’t face real issues head on - bc I didn’t have to. so living alone during lockdown & a pandemic has gifted me time to better myself as a person, friend, daughter, sister, aunt. 
.
.
I am grateful for hard + honest conversations. I’m grateful for feedback on how I’m perceived. how I made you feel. how something I said didn’t sit right. And I am particularly grateful for the strong FIERCE WOMEN bold enough to give it to me. not bc theyre biting back. but bc they care. 
.
.
so today - that’s my challenge. face the hard ones head on and look for some sort of silver lining. it’s there. dig deep & do better.

caption:
why is she posting about @kevinlove ?
.
.
for those of you who don’t know - Kevin Love is an NBA player for the Cleveland Cavs. yesterday he released an interview about his heart breaking struggle with mental illness. his suicidal thoughts, his feelings on inadequacy. his imposter syndrome. of all this he shared - here’s what got me :
.
.
Kevin love is 6’8”. He’s 251 pounds of solid muscle. he makes $31 million a year playing in the NBA. one paper Kevin Love is the physical definition of strong. he is undeniably successful. insanely healthy. 
.
.
yet, everyday he struggles with depression + on really bad days - suicidal thoughts. Kevin Love LOOKS (key word here) exactly the opposite of how he feels.
.
.
so it got me thinking - how often do we look at someone and judge them. how often do we NOT understand:
- the pretty girl that feels ugly
- the skinny person who feels fat
- the anxious person who seems calm
- the depressed person who seems happy
.
.
this reminder that we are NOT WHAT WE LOOK LIKE is exactly what we need. now. yesterday. tomorrow.
.
.
be kind. be compassionate. truly try to understand that how we look is so often not how we feel. & when you learn more - do better. 
.
.
.
.
.
.

easy, cheap and can store in the freezer for months

caption:
This is the serious face of a serious tree hunter. In previous years Otto fell asleep on our way to the neighbors tree farm. Isn't that how it always goes? He woke up grouchy, we'd grab a precut and head home. ⁠⠀
This year he was determined to find the best tree in the field. We ran from tree to tree for well over an hour until Otto found the one. It was missing about half it's branches in the middle but I thought meh might be good for bigger ornaments. ⁠⠀
Joe hacked it down, we yelled TIMBER and we drug it to the wagon. ⁠⠀
We carried our prized tree into the house only to discover we, once again, bought a tree 8 inches too tall. ⁠⠀

caption:
We headed out this weekend to pick up what I believe will be the last of our garland order. Each year we wrap the front porch and fireplaces in fresh greenery with big red bows. ⁠⠀
It's a tradition that I love coming home to each night and one that Joe curses because he's the one who has to hang it up and take it down. ⁠⠀
We have the tree up in the corner and will be spending the rest of the week decorating it with my delicate collection of Shiny Brite ornaments. ⁠⠀
I always treat myself to a "replacement box" because as gentle as Otto is with them, we are bound to have a few casualties. He loves to help and is so good about being careful that he gets devastated when one shatters. That's when we head for the back ups. ⁠⠀
I absolutely love that he always wants to help. My favorite is when Otto says "let me give you a hand with that mom" . ⁠⠀
I think the best part of decorating this weekend was explaining to Otto that we cut the tree down from outside and bring it inside. That was a conversation we had a few different times. Toddlers at Christmas might just be the best thing ever. ⁠⠀

caption:
I'm doing everything that I can to make this weird holiday season the best ever. I am fighting the sadness of the missing pieces this year but when I really think about the pieces I'm most sad about, they're not what the season is about at all. ⁠⠀
I am sad that this year Otto is head over heels in love with Christmas and we won't be doing the big family get togethers, the trips to the parades or even to sit on Santas lap. ⁠⠀
As a parent it's hard to not want to give your child the world especially at Christmas. However, Christmas is not about Santa, Christmas lights or toys. It's about the birth of Jesus and the meaning behind him coming into the world. It's been an interesting lesson trying to teach Otto. He loves the nativity scene but hasn't quite grasped that the baby's name is Jesus. He keeps referring to the set as Mary, Joseph and Lisa. As you can see we have some work to do. ⁠⠀
It's ok to be sad about the missing pieces but it's important to remember they don't complete the puzzle. ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland ⁠⠀

caption:
Thanksgiving 2020 is in the books and now we decorate and wait for Santa to come. ⁠⠀
We have been having an absolute riot with Otto this holiday season. He looks for Santa's sleigh every night before going to bed and every creak of the old roof could be him. ⁠⠀
I just love this age (despite all the stubbornness). ⁠⠀
When we were at the apple orchard this little shed was packed full of Christmas decorations and Otto was absolutely convinced that it was Santas workshop. He made us stand here and look for elves for a good ten minutes. ⁠⠀
His new favorite question other than asking someone's name is asking what they would like for Christmas. ⁠⠀
He says he wants a Paw Patrol Dino Rescue, Mom wants a purse and Dad wants a basketball. ⁠⠀
It's funny because Otto secretly also wants a basketball and knows his mama wants that purse. ⁠⠀
I'm excited to welcome in the holiday season. For now I'll be Black Friday shopping from the sofa! ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland #teamotto ⁠⠀

caption:
Thanksgiving plans are canceled but Thanksgiving goes on. With everything going on with Covid right now Joe and I thought it would be best for us to stay home. ⁠⠀
It really stings. ⁠⠀
It stings to have to avoid your own family on the holiday where you are most grateful for them. ⁠⠀
All is not lost. Joe and I frantically found some turkey legs at the local butcher and we went to the market yesterday to get some vegetables. Thanksgiving for three is on the menu today and we are going to celebrate the many blessings that have been given to us. ⁠⠀
We are getting dressed up for our "private" Thanksgiving feast before watching some football and going for a walk (weather pending). ⁠⠀
We never ever have a quiet holiday so we are trying to take this as hopefully the only opportunity we'll have for one. ⁠⠀
Wherever you are celebrating today friends I hope you are celebrating. I am thankful for you, my friends and family. God is good. Happy Thanksgiving. (and 2020, I'm most thankful you have only one month left)⁠⠀
⁠⠀

caption:
#sponsored. When it comes to Michigan’s fall and winter season you never know quite what to expect when you head out for the day. You can leave the house with sunny and warm weather only to arrive to your destination with cold rain or snow. I like to be warm but I also do not want to look like a snowman running around town. I was thrilled to partner with @Columbia1938 to try their Omni-Heat outerwear. I am wearing the Panorama Full Length Jacket in Black Camo with the Whirlibird Cuffed Beanie. The Panorama Jacket is lightweight but has the reflective silver dot lining that helps reflect my body's heat, keeping me warm without all of the bulky layers. It felt like a warm blanket around me all day and as a mom of a toddler, I loved all of the pockets. The Omni –Heat line is inspired from the heat reflective properties of NASA space blankets, which makes the material lightweight and functional for a variety of cold weather activities. I completed the look with the warm Whirlibird Cuffed Beanie. It’s nice to find a knit hat that can handle all of my curly hair. This hat had the perfect amount of stretch in it. Whether it’s running errands or nature walks in the woods with my family I love that I don’t have to pile on the layers when wearing pieces from the Omni-Heat collection.⁠⠀
#warmsmarter #adventuresinabbyland⁠⠀

caption:
Am I the only one who gets overly excited for birthday coupons during the month of their birthday? ⁠⠀
Every year I get my @freepeople birthday coupon and I splurge on a few key pieces to add to my wardrobe. When I look at some of my favorite sweaters still hanging in my closet, most of them were purchased with my birthday coupon. ⁠⠀
This sweater here was a birthday purchase and I'm honestly debating about getting one more color. I went back and forth about which size (medium or large) but in the end went with the large because I wanted to wear it as a sweater dress (and I don't like things too short). ⁠⠀
Typically this time of year I'm stocking up on sequins and tulle (and trust me there is still some of that going on) but since much of this winter will most likely be spent at home, I've leaned more into the cozy, well made sweaters. ⁠⠀
This sweater will be perfect for after the Thanksgiving feast! ⁠⠀

caption:
It's Friday and this elf and I have some work to do!⁠⠀
⁠⠀
This weekend's Christmas project is getting rid of the pumpkins on the porch, assembling my vintage aluminum tree, and getting a space ready for our real tree in the living room. ⁠⠀
This seems like not a big task but between Otto and I's collections... It's a task. ⁠⠀
Basically it involves finding a cute space to shove all of our crap until the tree comes down in January and the clutter can be restored to it's original resting space. ⁠⠀
Little does Otto know that when he's not looking I sneak toys he no longer plays with into the donation box. I would feel bad about it but I'm pretty sure that is the same thing Joe is doing to me. ⁠⠀
I will say though, spending all of this time at home I've tackled quite a few cluttered drawers. Folding, stacking and sizing and just throwing away has really helped (mostly my kitchen) stay organized. ⁠⠀
Organized being a term used loosely around here. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Regardless, It is a weekend of fun and family time (again) and I'm grateful for the sun that is forecasted our way! ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland #teamotto⁠⠀

caption:
This post is #sponsored by @michiganhhs. When Otto got his flu shot in September, we had to go to the toy store because he was so brave. It was hard not to smile because when Nurse J offered him a Mickey sticker after his shot he took the entire packet of them, hopped off the table and said, “We’re going to the toy store”. There is no debating with a toddler. Instead of picking out a small car like we usually do after a doctor’s appointment he told me it was a “special day” and picked out the semi hauler.  He proudly showed off his Band-Aid to everyone and told of his tales of bravery. Now, more than ever it’s important to get the flu shot. With COVID-19 already overwhelming our hospital systems it’s important to take as much pressure off of our healthcare workers as possible. A flu vaccination has been shown to reduce the risk of having to go to the doctor due to the flu by 40 to 60 percent. It’s also important to get the vaccination as soon as possible because it can take your body up to two weeks to build immunity to the flu after your shot. I was someone who never used to get a flu shot because I was young and healthy, but when Otto was born we learned more about protecting him and other vulnerable members of our society. When you get your flu vaccination you reduce the risk of spreading it to others who could be vulnerable themselves or taking care of vulnerable people. ⁠⠀
For more information about the flu vaccine check out my stories! #gotMiVax #IVaccinate⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland #teamotto ⁠⠀

caption:
Otto has been loving all of this time at home. We go for walks, play outside when it's not too cold and windy and he gets to play with his toys while his parents work. ⁠⠀
We have I think once again struck a balance of working from home. We had a breath of somewhat normalcy for a bit, but we know how to do this quarantine thing. ⁠⠀
It's not as strict as it was in the Spring. This three week long scale back still allows us to get take out, going for drives, going to the outdoor farmers markets and supporting small businesses in our area. ⁠⠀
This past Saturday we went to the fall farmers market in Holland and stocked up on cheese, root veggies, donuts and fresh garland. We are going to go back again on Wednesday to get more greenery because, you can never have enough greens!⁠⠀
We are nearing the end of 2020 and hopefully each day is a step in the right direction. Who knows what next year will look like but i'm holding on to hope that it only gets better from here! ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland #teamotto ⁠⠀

caption:
I miss Sunday brunches out. We are taking extra precautions with Covid again as cases are still on the rise. We still get take out from all of our favorites but I miss the noise, getting dressed up and enjoying a meal that I don't have to clean up. ⁠⠀
I'm buying stock in sweatpants and maxi dresses because 2021 is going to be the year of dining out. ⁠⠀
I keep telling myself that things continue to improve around here. Back in April when we would get take out we would wipe down all of the containers and the counter and basically wear gloves to move it to a plate. It seems crazy to look back on that but we have to to see how far we've come. Scientist, doctors and nurses know so much more about the virus now than they did when it first hit. ⁠⠀
I'm working hard on keeping positive and remaining optimistic that if we continue to do the work and be safe things will only continue to get better! Now...what's for dinner? ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland⁠⠀

caption:
I can't believe @TheFoundCottage has been open for an entire week now since our holiday reset. ⁠⠀
It was an interesting time to say the least. Decorating the shop for Christmas is the absolute funnest time at the store and typically the most stressful. This year compound the stress by 1000X. ⁠⠀
Owning a small business during 2020 has not been easy. We were shut down for three months this spring, allowed to open in steps by appointments and then limited capacity. ⁠⠀
We implemented hand sanitizing stations, temperature checks and all of the other hurdles to jump to keep our staff and customers safe and healthy. ⁠⠀
We are all holding our breath right now praying to be able to continue to stay open as much as the holiday season as possible. We thought we were scrappy in 2019... but learned what that really meant in 2020. ⁠⠀
If you are starting to do your holiday shopping please keep your local small business in mind. We are all here for you! ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland ⁠⠀

caption:
When times get tough I have a tendency to put my nose to the ground and just try to plough through it, not asking for help and not relying on my faith or God. It's gotten me in trouble so many times throughout my life and yet I continue to do it over and over again. ⁠⠀
I caught myself doing it again this week as we head into the holiday season around here. Otto is out of daycare for now, Joe and I are working in shifts. Things are so hectic! I caught myself continuously waking up at 4:30am and rather than trying to get much needed rest, sleep or even devotions, my computer was popped right open and I was plugging away at emails. ⁠⠀
Every. Single. Time. However rather than wait until things implode around me because of this behavior I'm trying to make small changes into how I approach this season. ⁠⠀
It has been so helpful to write out the following:⁠⠀
Daily Schedule ⁠⠀
5 tasks to tackle⁠⠀
2 things to do while on a brain break⁠⠀
The most important task though is taking time to be quiet and pray. ⁠⠀
My prayer today friends is that we all find peace, safety and health throughout this holiday and winter season. ⁠⠀
#adventuresinabbyland ⁠⠀

caption:
The best part of the morning is when Otto wakes up and looks to see who is still in the bed and then declares "It's best friends day!" (if all three of us are still there). So that is what today is. Best friends day. We are again going to take advantage of this sunny weather and play outside, maybe smoke some meat and act like it's still summer. ⁠⠀
We still have some bulbs to get in the ground and I think that these warm temps are sounding their warning bells.⁠⠀
I'm excited to get one more garden activity in without freezing my hands off.⁠⠀
It's yet another lesson the garden can teach you. Do the dirty work now and come spring you will hopefully have a bounty of beautiful blooms from the ground. ⁠⠀
I'm putting these bulbs in the ground because it confirms that spring will come eventually.⁠⠀
But for now we wait in the calm stillness of fall transitioning into winter.⁠⠀
Happy Sunday Friends. ⁠⠀

.

caption:
Some days are good and some are bad, but there is good in everyday.
.
I have been struggling with my anxiety  lately. More than what it usually is but I'm working on it.
.
The other week, completely loosing it with a full blown anxiety attack. 
Luckily, I was completely alone (never happens) 
I decided I didn't want to get out at one of the errands we had to run and the boys went with their dad.
An i got a moment to myself.. right?.. i guess you could say that....
Im grateful they didn't experience this with me.
.
I was fine one sec then out of no where when I say I lost it, I lost Control... out of No Where... 
Like a wave of emotions 
 +panic resulting in hyperventilating  turned into in tingling sensations  leading to  numbness and actual lose of control in part of my face...
Nothing like anything I've experienced before.
The worst of it lasting about 15 minutes but in all about 45 till I finally calmed down.
Then leaving me completely dranined,
And overwhelmed...
And they all came out with goodies to show and suspected nothing.
.
I'd like to think some days im super mom but some days I'm far from it.
Its easier said than done to just to release all the worry, anxiety, and stress..
What got me through that moment was opening up my Bible app reading scriptures and some serious time spent praying. While I was physically alone I didn't feel alone. 
.
Can all your worries add a single moment to your life?
Luke 12:25 
.
Worry weighs a person down; an encouraging word cheers a person up.
Proverbs 12:25 
.
Don’t be afraid, for I am with you. Don’t be discouraged, for I am your God. I will strengthen you and help you. I will hold you up with my victorious right hand.
Isaiah 41:10

caption:
Just checking in,
How is everyone?
----------------
I feel like it's been forever since I've been active. 
Its been a huge struggle, not gonna lie. I miss my insta fam💜
I've had to just take a break from all the negative and heartbreaks of the outside world.
.. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. .. ..
But at the same time, do you know how much more free time I've had?
You really dont realize how much time you spend on social media until you step back😳
(Gave me some serious mom guilt)
.
.
I've been more distant.
But also...
I've been searching.
I've been enjoying my time more with my babies.
I've been outside like every single day that I'm able.
I've started a mini garden.
I've been spending more time in my spiritual journey
I've been studying things I've put off for years.
I've been trying do evaluate my life, what I like what is going to change, what I want.
I've been planning.
...
So much going on over here in my life. (I'm sure the same goes for lots of others)
 Some much change is happening and coming.
But not even going into what's all taking place out in the world.
It's a little overwhelming but little by little is how I'm managing.
-----------------------------
Enough bout me though.
But what about YOU?
How are YOU?
I truly want to know how Your doing?
It seems like these days not many people stop to ask or even care.
.

caption:
-- 2 YEARS! --
I've had this swimsuit for 2 years!
I bought this swimsuit while I was pregnant thinking it would fit with the baby belly ended up not ever wearing it ...
and just now, 
I finally wore it for the first time. 
Not to be confused with trying it on.
(It just never fit right)
.
At the beginning of the year I decided I was going to make a few changes in my eating habits and start trying get serious bout losing some inches and  toning back up.
Really aiming to be healthier. 
Eating healthier, 
feel better..
Mentally,
Physically...
.
.
I've really got a little ways to get to my goal but I'm just now getting consistent with better food choices on a day to day basis, it's so easy to just reach for what is quick and cater to my picky eaters.
Its finally happening! (My picky eaters are also learning to try new foods)
And of course actually working out daily. 🙌
Just because 2020 isn't what we all imagined it would be, 
hasn't changed my mind about changes I wanted to make for my kids and myself 🤍
.
.
.

caption:
Spent the weekend celebrating my middle baby's Birthday! 
Who likes throwing Birthday partys?🙋‍♀️
not me..
While it may not look it, I was stressed to the max ! I even hate to admit it, but as the party was starting I was ready to cancel it. ( I was even experiencing some panic attacks) .
Problem. after problem kept occurring. 
When I thought I completely prepared staying up till the wee am hours, making sure it was all ready...
.
While the normal worry of who actually is gonna show up is the issue this time, everything else was the problem... and that..
.
 the heat, no shade and having nothing set up outside in time...
from me being late to even set up to constantly forgetting things having to leave several times (yes even with kids with the party guest), wrong size balloons (also them popping as quick as I'm getting them blown from the heat.. ending up having to do it all by myself bc hubs gets a mandatory call into to work.... on and on I could sit here 
and tell all the way this party did not go as I planned..
.
I felt as if I had failed (as I have felt the last several partys but this time way worse). The pressure and guilt (guilt from skipping one of his other partys as well...) was literally eating me alive.
.
maybe to you some of these were minor details but pretty major to me...at the moment.
.
but through it all I tried to smile and just apologize the whole time and I survived!
.
 By the end of it all I was exhausted and drained and started realizing my Perspective was all 
WRONG.
.
I put all the little footage I got together and was so overwhelmed, 
bc it confirmed everyone else seemed to be enjoying themselves and the kids were having fun despite all the 'stressors' I was experiencing .
Mamas try to not be so hard on yourself.
💥💥💥💥
IT DOES NOT HAVE TO BE A PINTEREST BIRTHDAY PARTY!
💥💥💥💥
^^^^^read that again^^^^
.
your kids will probably not remember the hiccups (though your in laws might😂I'm sure they understand)
.
Dont stress, its gonna turn out like its gonna turn out , sorry...but you cant control it all... just try to smile and enjoy it for what it is and these moments your creating bc you cant change the past.
❤
comments: Happy birthday to him!!! 🎉🎉🎉🎂; Sorry we missed it!!; You'd never know it you looked so happy and calm and all over it! I hate parties too especially hosting ANYTHING at my own house 🤣🤣 you did a great job and happy birthday little man! 🎂 #pleaseleaveby9; Gah!! I hate trying to plan the perfect party. I hope your little that the best day ever!!;

.
.
.
I’m lucky if we get 3-4 hour stretches at night and 1-2 hour naps during the day 💤 BUT earlier this week, Miles had a 6 hour stretch from 9pm-3am and it was basically the best thing that’s happened to me since he was born 🤣 Fingers crossed that this was not a one time thing 🤞🏼 If any mamas out there have any sleep tips, PUHLEASE share them with me💙
.
.
.

caption:
Even miracles take a little time ✨
.
.
.
And boy oh boy has this little one taken his sweet time 🕰 
.
.
.
When anyone says to me “omg your pregnancy has gone by so fast”, I literally laugh out loud and secretly want to slap them because it couldn’t be going by any slower 😅 I was 21 weeks along when the pandemic hit so I’ve basically been in quarantine for half my pregnancy which has really slowed time down 😝 
.
.
.

.
.
.
.

.
.

.
.
.

caption:
A few books on my shelf that have meant so much to me the last couple months. If you have given me a book, a song, a poem, or an impression, please know you are my people, and it has meant the world to me. ♡   ⠀
⠀
Before everything happened with Collin I had listened The Dutch House. I loved it so much I ordered a hard copy and planned on reading it again as soon as it arrived. I am not a re-reader so *that* is how much I loved it. I jot little notes down for the reviews and pulled them up to write this post. It had said “The sweetest story of a funny brother and his sister. Will break and remake your heart.” Not sure I can bring myself to re-read it right now, if you’ve read it you know why, but no wonder I loved it so much. Also, Tom Hanks’ narration is actual perfection.⠀
⠀
The other three books were gifted to me and I would highly recommend if you’re going through a loss or need a way to support someone who is. Francis Weller is a freakin’ treasure. And the Year of Magical Thinking is as well. And Mother’s Milk is a specific kind of comfort, but something that has been on my mind so much. ⠀
⠀
I posted the rest of my book reviews on my site, 2 of which made my top 3 for 2020 which were The Dutch House, American Dirt and The Heart’s Invisible Furies. What was your favorite read this year? #smallfrybooks #bookstack
