caption:
FAMILY - deep breaths.
⠀
My single greatest teacher in this life. It has taught me to love without expectation, to forgive and protect, to apologize and try again, to set boundaries and hold to them. My most important lesson being to honor and respect where my family is in their own healing. To not push or prod, to just let them be. I feel really blessed (and poor, as it took a lot of therapy💸) to feel nothing but love. Is it easy? Heck no. But, I hold no anger or ill will.⠀

 When my parents split the divorce was nasty. I can’t imagine divorce as a kid, but as a young adult, it hurt. A lot. We lost our sense of home, and we all sort of spun out into our own directions. Collin was the one who came to me and said, “That’s it! We’re starting Kartchner 2.0. For whoever wants to show up and be a family.” And limping and bruised we did just that. We all had to step into roles we weren’t necessarily built for, and lift where we stood, even when hurting and angry — we showed up. ⠀
Some of my most sacred experiences came from the ashes of a family burned. Walking my sister down the aisle. Standing by my brother as he got sober. Sobbing with my sisters in a pile on the floor at my house, unable to stand another second, heartbroken for our brother. And I’m only just skimming the surface of whatever Collin has in store for me now. How amazing to know the some of our best days haven’t happened yet?!⠀
⠀
It’s not a great feeling to know that the complexities of your family are being discussed on forums and by strangers (Not reading word of it, don’t worry.) No one except us will ever know the truth, and that’s okay, because truly it’s nunya. 😉⠀
But, I just wanted to share this today because I know the Holidays for many are painful. It’s hard to see seemingly picture perfect families and wonder why we struggle so hard. But I know firsthand there is beauty in the ashes. There can be healing even when no one is saying sorry. And you are not alone. 

To my parents, Chad, Keira, Charity, Tim, Collin, Liz, Russ, Bethany, Lauren, Casey and everyone we’ve given life to since, thank you for being my family. I love you all. #givethanks #lovelikecollin

caption:
When we first moved to our small town a couple years ago I prayed around the clock that my boys would find friends here. They have now, but at the time, it wasn’t smooth sailing. I would take it super hard when they didn’t hit it off with someone, and at my lowest, felt like we made a big mistake. If we were supposed to be here, shouldn’t it be easier?⠀
⠀
Not long after, a neighbor Abby mentioned having Cal play with her son. I truly couldn’t fit all of the challenges Ty and his little body have faced in this caption. Countless surgeries, specialists, medications, and more.  He is unique in every way and I thought to myself and maybe even told Abby🙈, “Cal’s just not your guy.” He’s an introvert and a loose cannon, and truly DGAF’s about what anyone thinks of him. He once told me he wouldn’t play with a boy because he smiled too much.😆🙇🏼‍♀️ I thought I would save potentially hurting Abby or Ty’s feelings, and to be honest, avoiding my own embarrassment at what might happen. I had long abandoned trying to fit Cal into the mold I had made for him. What I thought the world needed him to be. 
⠀
Gratefully, Abby didn’t give up and we finally got them together. Fast forward a couple of years and the Frames count ourselves so incredibly lucky. Lucky that we get to know and love Ty. Who makes every single one of us laugh until we have tears running down our faces. Who tells me I am so beautiful every time he sees me. Who entertains and plays with us through every church meeting, for hours in our home, and most importantly brings out the very best in Cal. The most happy, patient, imaginative, focused, silly Cal.⠀
⠀
Ty is my reminder of so many things: ⠀
•To get out of my kids’ way. ⠀
•Let them lead, but champion them every step of the way. (Abby taught me that)⠀
•That their (my, your) potential is limitless. ⠀
•We are not our bodies, we are so, so much more. ⠀
•To see things as God sees them. Because He answers our prayers and blesses us in his perfect way, even if we don’t have the eyes to see it perfectly all the time.
⠀
#givethanks

caption:
The last day Collin and I spent together I had texted him to see if Quincey would come to the pool with me. I was still in the weeds having my 4th baby and didn’t feel up to the challenge to take them swimming alone. He wrote back, “YES! But we’re all coming!!” 🤍 Just him and I and our kids. ⠀
⠀
He took Raleigh down the slide 15 times at least. Swam with the boys, wowed them with his diving board tricks (a jack knife right under the lifeguard getting them drenched was his specialty) and then while he thought no one was watching headed over to the concession stand. ⠀
He prepaid for 50 snow cones and then went to the corner to laugh to himself. 😆 News traveled fast and soon a line of stoked kids trailed out to the gate. 🍧 There are moments when I slip into shame that the last day we spent together was 2 months ago. Sure we texted memes like it was our job, but it’s not the same right? How did I let that happen?! But then, I have to shake myself, and then I am overwhelmed with gratitude. It was the very best, last day. 

#lovelikecollin ⠀

••• This story was taken from the life sketch I wrote for our family’s memorial. It’s on my site. A love letter from a sister to her big brother. Sharing these stories has been such a big part of my processing this whole week, thank you for being here and listening. I hope you don’t feel like you have to keep sending condolences. I don’t want to bring anyone down!! I just love talking about him, and it’s brought me so much comfort. So thank you for that. ♡

caption:
We’re all seeing his effect now, so you can imagine his effect when he dedicated 24/7 to the cause he believed in most. He served a two year service mission to Taipei, Taiwan for our church and at the time, you leave your family and you can write letters and call on Christmas and Mother’s Day. That’s it. Your day to day schedule is devoted to studying scripture, serving others, sharing the message of our church, working with those interested to join and, if all goes well, baptize them to be a member. In a notoriously uninterested country, Collin seemed to change hearts in droves. ⠀
⠀
But in order to do that he had to leave his family (and Liz, they were dating for awhile by now!) for two years. You all know our side of the family is complicated and messy. We put the fun in dysfunctional. It has been for many years, and Collin was my rock through it all. The one I could turn to, forget my troubles and have a laugh. When he left in 1998, I was 12 and inconsolable. I cried every day for weeks. ⠀
⠀
Tarzan was the movie of the day and Phil Collins gave us “You’ll be in my heart.” I recorded it to a tape and listened to it over and over and over, crying into the carpet. I harassed him via letters if he had heard it (are we seeing a theme?) and when he went to the airport to fly to Taiwan I got a phone call at the house. ⠀
⠀
“Hello?” ⠀

“...Come stop your crying, it will be alright...” 😂😭⠀
⠀
His voice sings through the receiver. And we both cry. I cry because I want my brother back. He cries, I’m sure, because he’s scared, he is stepping into the unknown, and he knows what he has to do. ⠀
⠀
His mission is bigger than than me. I know that now. It doesn’t make it better, I would happily keep him to ourselves and deny all the good he can do. I’m angry. But now his endless talents know no limits. He is unbound, he is all love. ⠀
⠀
Let him work in you. Let his message change your life. Know that he (and I) believe in a loving God, and even in all our crazy, our family will be together again. I wish it were tomorrow. #lovelikecollin

caption:
⠀
People probably don’t realize, but Collin is an amazing musician (save some talents for the rest of us.) He composed piano music, sang in the church choir and led the primary music for years. Guitar, cello, ukulele, you name it. ⠀
⠀
When I got married in 2005, Coldplay had just released “Fix You” and I was obsessed with it. I kept harassing him to learn it on the piano. And then at our wedding he surprised me and played and sang it for me. It has the register for a prepubescent altar boy, but he did it anyway. And I bawled.⠀
⠀
Fast forward to 10.20.2020, Russ and I are at our 15 year anniversary dinner eating at this hip restaurant (HSL, go it’s so good) and it’s playing banger after banger, all new indie rock songs that I’d have to secretly Shazam under the table. And then all the sudden, Fix You comes on. And we look at each other and we just smile. What are the odds? How amazing! It made us so freaking happy. ⠀
⠀
I didn’t know until later, but it was playing just as Collin left us. And to me, it’s clear as day. It’s not a wedding song. But it was a big bear hug 15 years in the making and it has brought me so much comfort. ⠀
⠀
Lights will guide you home⠀
And ignite your bones ⠀
And I will try to fix you.⠀
⠀
#lovelikecollin — I know I keep asking you guys for stuff but, please share your memories. I (and I’m sure the rest of the family) would love to read them all someday when we need his big bear hugs most.

caption:
If I just keep running, moving, arranging, feeding, maybe the truth of this won’t ever hit me. And then when I finally sit and close my eyes, everything behind my lids is horrifying. We have so many questions, but mostly just the one: WHY. We want answers, but it seems we can’t have them. Not yet anyway. In a world where everything is instant, we are learning to wait. To sit in it, to feel it all. ⠀
⠀
In the waiting, I have seen and felt more goodness, more generosity, more support, love, and the true and lasting effect that Collin really had. It overflows and its ripple and radius has touched us all so deeply. ⠀
⠀
I asked you to show up for him, for Liz and his kids, to let them hear us. And all your voices joined together and ROARED. I will never, ever forget it. I scrolled the donations with his kids and they laughed and cried and their jaws dropped. BLESS YOU ALL. Please pray for them, pray for Liz. If grief is the evidence of love, we now get a sense just how much they loved each other. And since there really is no right way to grieve, I might just have to share every last thing I love about my brother until my lungs give out. Thank you for waiting with us, for holding space, and for loving him like we do. xo, Emily #lovelikecollin
comments:
Losing a loved one is always hard - but more so when it’s unexpected. My Dad just passed away in August. It was a long time coming but the grief is still unavoidable because we love him and miss him sooo much. It comes in waves.  I’ve found that when a wave hits - if I can take a break to lay in my hammock or in a quiet room and let myself feel/cry while I listen to his voice in some old recordings I have of him - I’m more quickly comforted. 
I’m so thankful that Collin was so vocal and so visible so that you have a wealth of recordings to draw from. Praying for and with your family.; At 32 I lost my brother to a car accident. He was my world. That was 1985. In 2016 I stumbled upon Collin, a guy on insta, having a laugh. It was like finding my brother all over again. I instantly bonded to him. My friends and family thought I was weird as I referred to him as my friend Collin. “Collin did this, Collin did that. Collin is exactly how Mike was. Imagine the two of them doing this together! Listen to Collin saving kids!” I DM’d him regularly hoping to lift his spirit and encourage his work. The story where he sat behind the fast food restaurant and sobbed, gutted me. He deleted it very quickly but it was a glimpse of the burden a loving, giving heart held. I am almost as sad now as when my brother died. But it’s not because I knew him, or even ever met him, but just chatted on occasion and said many many prayers for him and his family through the years. His love of life will not be forgotten. His smile and bright blue eyes will forever be in our hearts. I will do my best to love like Collin, hug like Collin. I can because of the brother gone in 1985 as well. Those brothers, those loving guys, leave us to find our way, and still live on in us. ❤️💔❤️; 😩😩😩😩😩; “Grief is the evidence of love” ♥️♥️♥️;

caption:
FIFTEEN YEARS!! We’ve been doing a lot of reminiscing over here this year with this milestone afoot. One moment that keeps coming to mind from all the way back when we were engaged... 

I had (what I thought was) a stroke. Searing headache, lost feeling in my face, down my arms, legs and stomach, with slurred speech. I know now and am very familiar with these aura migraines, but then I had no clue what was happening to me. 

I crawled into bed, terrified and crying. Russ laid next to me, stroking my hair and sang me my favorite, most comforting gospel song. 

 “Abide with me ‘tis eventide, the night is coming on... Within my heart a welcome guest, within my home abide. O savior stay this night with me, behold tis eventide.” 

Marriage, for us, hasn’t been some magic cure-all, that solves all pain or loneliness.  But he has been the closest thing in my life to Christlike love. A witness to all the good, hard, and quiet. He has never tried to own or change or hurt. Just made himself the most welcome guest of my heart. That 19 year old girl didn’t know how good she had it, but she knows now. Happy anni, Russ Frame ♡

caption:
I read the reports of 865,000 women leaving the workforce in September and couldn’t help but cry. Not because every woman or mother should have a job, but because it has become untenable for nearly a million of us. 💔 (4x more then men, but my heart goes out to them, too.) ⠀
⠀
It has felt impossible to pursue dreams and manage the fallout of a pandemic. To take care of our most important priorities 👶🏼 and have even a moment for other ones, too. If you are there: I am there with you. ⠀
⠀
In September, I was ready to throw the towel in on my own small business. Scratching my head at how to pay a mortgage, bills, juggling government guidelines, screaming clients and just plain defiant ones. All while working for free just to keep doors open. ⠀
⠀
I see you fighting, we’re fighting too. In all our faults, the human spirit really is uncrushable, I think 2020 proves that. 😆 We might be limping, we might be taking a seat on the bench for a bit, but these circumstances say nothing about you or me and what we’re capable of. If anything it has taught me that even if I don’t make another dollar in this lifetime, my worth does not change. It says nothing about our ideas, our work ethic, our intrinsic value. Take your rest, shop small, unclench that jaw and know that you are loved. — ♡ Emily

caption:
Hamilton will always hold a special place in my heart. ❤️ 
Back in 2015, during an interview with Joss Whedon, he mentioned being inspired by seeing the early previews of Hamilton. I wrote about. Lin-Manuel Miranda tweeted out my article. It was picked up by BroadwayWorld.com. Keep in mind this all happened during my first film press junket ever, so it was kind of a big deal! 😱
A year later I was at the press junket for Moana. That’s when I got turned into a Twitter meme because LMM tweeted out a picture of everyone in the interview that caught me making a funny face. Mildly embarrassing, but then he tweeted out a link to my article about it and it became one of my favorite memories. (I also got in a tiny bit of trouble for singing “You’ll Be Back” in the hallway of the hotel where the press junket was taking place, but that’s a whole ‘nother story...)
All of this happened without me ever having seen #Hamilton in person. (Although I’d listened to the cast recording and mix-tapes a ridiculous number of times.) Finally, in 2018, I made it to the theater and was in the room where it happened. It lived up to every bit of the hype. 😍
I’m so excited that everyone can now purchase Hamilton merch at @BoxLunchGifts. They’ve got t-shirts, totes, mugs and more! And when theaters are finally open again, I’ll be there. Probably singing “You’ll Be Back” again....
#BLxHamilton #BLSponsored
#hamiltonmusical #alexanderhamilton #broadway #linmanuelmiranda #hamiltonmemes #hamiltonbroadway

I visited Walt Disney World for the first time when I was five years old. I don't know if photos exist from that trip and I don't know if I met any characters. 
I do, however, remember that my souvenir was a plush #WinnieThePooh wearing a little red bib instead of a t-shirt. 
While those first #WDW memories are fuzzy, my first #Disneyland memories are crystal clear. It helps that they are all from the last five years. 😉
My first character photos are from breakfast at #PlazaInn. It seems fitting that one of them is with Winnie The Pooh. It's also fitting that is a hug since his are what I'm missing the most right now.  #DisneyMagicMoments

caption:
Easter is a little different this year, but I partnered with @hersheys to create a fun way to celebrate at home. I was able to dig into my baking supplies and create some super cute (if I do say so myself) Reese's Eggs Easter Bunnies! 🐰
I made ears out of modeling chocolate and used icing to glue on a sprinkle nose and candy eyes. I also broke out my food color pens to make little whiskers. 🖊️
I'm now fully prepared for my bestie to tell me they look like mice. 🐭 What can I say? I always make my Bunnies with little ears. 😂
Stay home and stay safe this Easter,  and create some fun new traditions with your family! 🐣

caption:
Let’s talk Christmas traditions! 🎄 Ryan and I have so many it’s not even funny, two of them involving ornaments! Each year we pick out a new ornament at the store that sort of represents us that year, or just who we are in general. Also, we try to collect ornaments everywhere we travel. So, when we look back on all of our ornaments, we remember previous years and places we have been together and all of the memories we have made. It’s kinda cheesy, but we love it! We have two other trees we decorate in our home, and they are “pretty” and “styled”, but this tree is definitely our favorite ❤️❤️❤️ Head to our stories to see which ornaments we selected this year and a peek at some others we have! What are some of your Christmas traditions? ⬇️
.
.
#diyhomedecor #farmhousedecor #farmhouseliving #farmhousestyle #farmhousechic #farmhouse #vintagedecor #farmhouseinspired #interiordesign #modernfarmhouse #modernrustic #joannagaines #farmhousedesign #farmhousefeatures #homedecor #decor #rustic #shiplap #fixerupper #diy #rusticdecor #hgtv
comments: We try to collect ornaments from places we go too! ALSO, we get each of our kids a new ornament every year to represent them or their year - this year we got a ballet one for my daughter who started dance class, we got buzz Lightyear for my son because he dressed up as Buzz for Halloween, and we got one that's an exact replica of one of my 2yo's favorite toys! I also try to get a family one and one for my husband each year... His is a bike because he loves cycling! My mom did this for us growing up and I love looking back on mine from when I was a kid like you did in your stories 😂😍; I hated the personalized ornaments until... my late daughters daycare did them.. she come home with finger print reindeer and other handmade things, at the time I let her put them on the tree thinking they would just go up in her room at Christmas time not knowing that would be her last Christmas. Now, we spend the week before Christmas making salt dough ornaments and Christmas Eve painting them with our children. Our tree is full of homemade ornaments that our kids make and I wouldn’t change it for anything. ❤️💔; I started that tradition when my kids were born. Each year an order ament for them. Then my husband and I added to that tradition. The family tree has ornaments dated back to 1994. ❤️; Love that tradition, also love the matching pjs 😍;

I’ve always wanted a flocked tree but I’m afraid my kiddos would pick it all off!; @emilykrobi king of Christmas trees the flocking stays on super well is non toxic!; @newbuild_newlyweds PERFECT! I have 4 kids under 7 and 2 pups!; I know that's the Samsung frame TV, do you have to pay extra to have access to the photos you display on it?;

This week we’re talking all things Filipino food! One of my favorite go to meals is Sinigang🍲 when we make it we add, spinach, onions, tomato, pork, this sour mix you see me holding and sometimes egg plant. There are different variations of it that may include beef, shrimp, fish or chicken...Swipe to see a picture of what Sinigang look likes *i did not make the soup in that photo*
•
Some common Filipino food that you may be familiar with; Lumpia, Pancit, Adobo, Lechon and if you’re really feeling ya self...Balut!
•

caption:
A party without cake is just a meeting🤪

Anyone else bake to relieve stress? Behold the brownie, Oreo Ice-cream cake with a Nutella-Oreo layer and topped with Ganache and more brownies and Oreos (of course!)

How I built it:

1) bake two brownie layers, I used @ghirardelli brownie mix

2) line a deep pan with parchment paper and transfer cooled brownie layer to the bottom

3) top brownie with Nutella and Oreo pieces

4) layer softened Oreo icecream on top 

5) freeze overnight

6) top icecream with Oreo crumbles and second brownie layer

7) drizzle chocolate ganache and decorate with brownies and Oreos!!

caption:
A boo-tiful apple pie 👻👻

After a trip to the orchard we had more apples than we knew what to do with. So it was only fitting to make some apple pies with a little Halloween flare🦇

This is my mom’s recipe that’s been in the family for over 30 years now! 

🥧Pie crust: 🥧

4 c flour
1 1/2 c shortening (crisco)
1/4 c butter (cold and cubed)
Mix first then add:
1 egg
1/2 c cold water
2 tsp salt
1 tbs sugar
2 tbs vinegar
Form 5 balls put in fridge 

🍎Filling: 🍎
6 cups apple sliced
1 1/2 tsp cinnamon 
1/4 c flour
1 c sugar
Mix with apples
(This makes one pie)
Put 3 tbs on top of the filling before pie crust top

🔥Bake at 425 40-50 mins if fresh

❄️You can also freeze pie & then bake at 350 for 90 mins

Do you have any favorite family recipes?

Strength. Muscles. Power. 
Recovery. Nutrition. FOOD. Fuel.

For so much of my life, I hated my body. I didn’t understand why my legs were “bigger” (read: strong AF and athletic) than the women I saw in magazines or on the TV. I didn’t think stomach rolls were normal. I yearned to have a *perfect* body. Those words I listed above ⬆️ simply weren’t in my vocabulary. I thought being a fast runner meant you had to be skinny.

I struggled with RED-S for years…because I just wasn’t fueling enough. I didn’t understand how damn important food is. I rowed 4 years in college (somehow) without any injuries…but when I started running, that all changed. I started getting exactly 1 stress reaction each year. Tibia (x2). Femur. Sacrum.

Enough was enough. I started getting my blood tested regularly with @insidetracker and realized that understanding nutrient levels from the inside out was crucial to performance and staying healthy.

Because of InsideTracker’s easy-to-understand platform (swipe to take a look), I educated myself on Vitamin D health, iron/ferritin levels, and other biomarkers I had never heard of before, nor would’ve known to ask about. Yes, I could’ve gone to my doctor and inquired to get blood testing; but because of personal insurance limitations, InsideTracker was infinitely easier and timelier for me.

I turned around my nutrition and started eating much more red meat (and more food, in general!) I started supplementing with Vitamin D and magnesium. Recovery became an essential part of the equation. I took control over my health and haven’t looked back. As a result: I’m running faster and lifting heavier than before. 💪🏻

caption:
Riding that PR high today! Yesterday was supposed to be a 5k TT with some local women (similar to what we did a couple weeks ago) - but we decided to call it off with the rising COVID numbers. We all were bummed, but knew it was the best/safest decision.

I was tempted to do another solo 5k, but my coach suggested I pick another distance, if I was up for it. My body felt great all week, and I had done a mini taper...so when I woke up Saturday morning, I decided to shoot my shot at a 10k! I've only run a few 10ks in the past, and always thought of them as being really hard; I've never come anywhere close to low or sub-40...so going into it, thought a sub-40 would be a huge accomplishment.

I honestly have only run a handful of tempos with this new training...so thinking about a fast ~40 minutes of pain was VERY intimating. So it's probably good that I made a day-of decision. 😂 I chose to run on a track because I wanted the accurate distance and running laps seemed way more digestible than tackling 6 miles on the road (Type 2 fun...)

My goal was to shoot for 200s in 45-47 and quarters in 91-95...so when the slower range of that felt fast, I just told myself to hang on and stay tough. I hit the 5k in 19:26 and knew I'd def hit sub-40, and possibly even sub-39 (🤯) - but to stay relaxed. I literally said to myself, "don't be stupid and you'll PR no matter what." I felt my legs get lactic-y and lose power way before the aerobic system did; but was still able to find that second gear for the final mile, closing the final quarter in 82. 🌶

Special thanks to @bose for helping propel me to my best 10k yet! The new Sport Earbuds sound amazing, DO NOT FALL OUT (🎉), are sweat/weather resistant...and, best of all, the battery life is impressive - up to 5 hours per charge. They also take phone calls (a must for me) and the audio for both the caller and receiver is great. As a lover of music/podcasts while running and lifting, I'm so thankful for these little buds! #BosePartner #BoseEarbuds #10kPR

caption:
Full send into a new week. Pain face included...because it's 2020. 💥

Monday is actually my favorite day of the week (weird, I know). It means there's a whole week left to get shit done. But if I'm not efficient with my time, I start having a mini internal panic attack by Wednesday. As a perfectionist and someone who puts a lot of pressure on herself to succeed, the only way I survive is via mini goals and to do lists.

There's only 7 more Mondays left in 2020 and we get to make the decision as to how they unravel. There are so many things that have spiraled out of control in 2020; staying within ourselves to control what we can is at a new level of importance these days.

For the rest of the year, I'm choosing to control my attitude and my attention to details with my day-to-day tasks (coaching and personal training). Instead of looking at this year, thinking about how miserable it was, I'm choosing to look at the opportunities and silver linings it brought. 

So what are you choosing to control in these final weeks? What gratitude can you start honing in on as the end of another year approaches? #fullsend #happymonday #lululemonambassador #thesweatlife

caption:
My first 5k race on the track last Saturday was an experience!  As someone who never had any interest racing/getting faster in shorter distances…I’ve gotta say, it’s been really fun working on turnover. And having the opportunity to run against others in a safe, socially-distant race setting was a privilege!

Some of the main things I learned from the race:
▫️You ALWAYS have more than you think you do. The mind goes WAY before the legs do.
▫️Passing someone in a track race is a little scary, because you really have to commit to it. And it’s also a bit overwhelming trying not to trip the people around you.
▫️There was a lap where I passed a high school girl and told her to stick to my shoulder and hang on. That lap went by faster than any other lap - turns out when you focus on doing something for the good of someone else, it really does make your own effort feel easy.
▫️5ks are painful.

Today, I’m sharing a full recap on my blog (link in profile); and I also include a quick review of the @brooks Adrenaline GTS 21, delivered to me from @zappos! caption:
Q: Which strength exercises should I do as a runner?
A: ALL OF THEM

If there's one thing you need to remember, it's that lifting and strength training will make you a stronger overall ATHLETE. Period. The goal as a runner should not be, "let me just get this calf stronger," or "let me work on my 'bad' knee."

You have to lift heavy to be strong and to move/perform like the badass athlete you are. Period.

This means upper and lower body. When you bench or row, there are absolutely carryovers into running, and I'm not just talking about using your arms to propel you up a hill. Upper body work yields major neuromuscular adaptations that will make your trunk and back stronger. The stronger you are up the entire chain, the better you're able to combat the forces that pound on your joints with every running step. 

It's not about adding lifting to your training randomly. It's literally about realizing that strength is part of your training, and it must fit in if you want to be successful long term. 

Video is of my PR bench of 120 lbs last night. Pow. 💥 #stronglikearunner #runstrong

caption:
A year ago, I was 4 months postpartum. This weekend I ran the fastest 5k of my life - 55 seconds faster vs. pre-baby. But recovering from having a baby was above and beyond my expectations; that shit is HARD.

I felt so weak.
My back hurt.
I was tired from lack of sleep.
My boobs hurt.
Any previous injury i ever had suddenly popped up and intensified (HELLO cyst in my wrist + a neuroma in my foot).
Running wasn't enjoyable because it hurt. So I didn't for a long time.

The secret to coming back stronger? There is none. I threw out expectations. I rode the lows with the highs. I took unplanned rest days. I asked for help. I ignored pace. I stopped comparing myself to my old self. And I kept believing.

This process took a while. So if there's one thing you remember it's this: good things take time and a lot of belief. Keep showing up. Reassess every few months. Make sure you're seeing small improvements, and remember to celebrate the crap out of them. And find people who support you along the way and you'll never stop growing. #belief #perspective #swapteam #liftrunperform

Post-run must haves: a big squeeze from my sweet cherub and FUEL! 😍

After a run, I’m awful about stretching and rolling; and truthfully, the research is mixed on whether you “have” to do either - you do you, boo. If it feels good? Go for it. But one thing I never skimp is post-workout nutrition.

Typically I’ll grab a shake or bar with 20 grams of protein immediately post run; but if I know I won’t eat a meal soon, then I’ll also snag a @clifbar to temper the runger.

What’s the best carb/protein/fat breakdown for an endurance athlete? Well - it’s out of my scope to recommend that; but research has confirmed, “Glycogen supercompensation results from a combination of ample rest, reduced training volume, and the consumption of a high-carbohydrate diet.”

(AKA - CARBS ARE YOUR FRIEND - particularly those that are high-quality, easy to digest, and nutrient-rich). So eat up! And remember that your actions/decisions in between runs (recovery) is just as important as the run itself. #clifbarAmbassador #sponsored

Ref: Murray et al., 2018

caption:
In-run fueling is a low hanging fruit for SO MANY athletes. The concept of eating 200 kcal/hr seems simple (a GENERAL suggestion) - but actually training your stomach for that is…another story. But remember that the stomach is trainable, just like the rest of the body. Eating while running is typically not an innate trait we’re born with…but we can teach ourselves how! 

So, in general, here are some tips for athletes when it comes to getting better about fueling on the run:
▪️Don’t be afraid of trying different fuel types. Every body is going to respond differently to different energy sources.
▪️Eat before you run! That means eating breakfast should be a non-negotiable.
▪️There are no rules about HOW to eat while running (eg - you don’t need to chow it all down at once) - if you need to take small bites/sips of whatever you’re fueling with, then use that strategy!

Thanks to @clifbar for providing fuel that keeps me going during the day and also before my runs! It’s become an absolute staple in my diet, and its ingredients are simple, yet satisfying…so I know it’s a “safe” pre-run option for my gut.

Need to work on fueling? Make sure you save this post and start working on it NOW! 🤗

caption:
How it started vs. how it's going 😳

From 5/7 seat as a collegiate rower (who majored in marketing) ➡️ running enthusiast (who coaches people to be faster and stronger and owns an online coaching service).

2009 - graduated from college. 👩🏻‍🎓
2010 - my boyfriend dumped me and post-collegiate rowing didn't pan out...so I signed up for my first marathon. 🤷🏼‍♀️
2011 - ran another marathon and missed a BQ by a minute. 😭
2012 - got married! 👰🏼
2013 - hired a coach. Hit my BQ that spring. Started realizing that consistent training works. 🤯
2014 - ran Boston! 🦄
2015 - got laid off from my job in fashion marketing, then decided to change career paths and transition to coaching. Started by interning at local facilities and eventually got a job by the end of the year. 🎉
2016 - started run coaching. 🏃‍♀️
2017 - founded @liftrunperform while dealing/figuring out a frustrating lower back injury. 👩🏼‍💻
2019 - had a baby!! 👶🏼
2020 - pregnancy only aggravated the lower back pain, so discovered strength training on a whole new level. Continued to grow/learn as a coach. Thankful every day for the ability to run and have an entire new perspective in the sport. ❤️

There are inevitably lots of ups and downs in every journey; but learning from every low has brought highs that are even higher than before. Proud of this journey and for how far I've come, on so many levels. Have you been able to learn from your lows? #rememberyourwhy #perspective #newweek

caption:
“Do you eat less on rest days?”

That’s ⬆️ a question I get asked a lot…and my answer: NO. In fact, some rest days (or days where I’m lifting and not running), I find myself craving/eating more.

Why?

Often rest/non-run days come after a hard effort or workout…so the likelihood of waking up the day after a hard effort and being in an energy deficit is fairly high.

And with the intention of the days around hard effort days being RECOVERY (because training should be polarized) - the #1 thing that is going to help with recovery is sleep…followed by a balanced diet of fats/carbs/protein. When training is at a high stress/load, the last thing someone would want to do is further that stress on the body by not eating enough.

Training like an athlete also means EATING like an athlete. And that’s something I (finally) take seriously, after years of unhealthy habits during high school/collegiate athletics.

So yeah. I’m smiling in this photo because I’m about to eat my daily @clifbar after my lifting session, and you could say I’m pretty jazzed about it. 🤗

caption:
Breakthroughs aren't about luck. They're about hard work. The kind of work that happens when you keep showing up, even when it sucks...even when you're tired...even when you wonder why you're doing it anymore.

They're about repeating positive behaviors.
Eliminating distractions.
Asking for help, and realizing that you don't know it all.
Finding the positivity out of every situation.
Patience.
Embracing the discomfort.
Loving yourself.

Along the way, people will shut you down. They'll insinuate that you and your goals aren't good enough. They'll project their issues and agenda onto you. And you might believe these people...the narcissists. It's human nature that their words will creep into your head and psych you out. In fact: these people will straight up knock you down.

But it's up to you to keep showing up. And if you do get knocked down...to learn from it. To persevere and let it fuel your fire. Because your own motivation runs so much deeper.

So to you who is working hard towards something: whether it's a running, professional, educational, or personal goal. Keep going. Keep repeating the behavior that’s moving you closer to your goals. Do the hard shit and lean into it. Realize your self worth and keep showing up for yourself - because you deserve it.

caption:
How do you define success? That's something I think about a lot, especially this past weekend when I visited home (Central NY) for the first time in well over a year. The trip felt extra special this time, because my son is old enough to explore and adventure and see what I saw growing up.

Our definition of success changes all the time. When I was younger, I defined success by having friends...playing in a sports game...getting an after school job...going to college. These days, I look at success as being able to relax on the weekend...accomplishing my training goals...being present for my baby.

James Clear writes, "Hard work is rarely enough without good strategy, but even the best strategy is useless without hard work."

I learned about hard work as a kid growing up. I was taught that working hard would bring success. And success should be something that's sought out because achieving goals tends to yield happiness. But what I've learned as I've gotten older is that success is measured differently each season of life; and that's ok/normal.

And what happens when we fail? I used to fear failure; I think as a product of my upbringing. Failure meant I wasn't enough. It meant my hard work was a waste.

But...turns out...I (we) am (are) all enough.

Hard work and success is what YOU make of it. Hard work makes us more resilient, stronger, and more determined. You generate your own attitude...you determine how you use your 24 hours in the day...you decide whether to take action or to settle. caption:
15 months postpartum vs. 3 months.
Then: 70 lbs (second slide)
Today: 105 lbs (first slide)

And the third photo in this series was from my first stroller run, exactly one year ago. It was a 2 mile run, and I felt like I was dying the entire time. My SI joint also hurt post-run, and this run was the catalyst for putting a firm halt to any further running and dedicating myself to strength.

Yesterday I ran a 12 miles with a workout in the middle, painfree, and feel the best I‘ve felt in years. But it took MONTHS of 10-30 minute runs, hill strides, and soooo much patience.

Not shown in between these photos: Tears. Lows. Highs. Feeling discouraged. Realizing that I’m stronger than I thought. Not believing I’d ever run fast again. Going to the gym super late, after the baby was sleeping. Finding a new purpose to training. PRing, both in running and lifting.

Instagram is filled with flashy photos, videos, and journies that seem incredible on the surface. Don’t forget there’s a lot behind the scenes that is never shown or talked about here. For me, postpartum fitness has been about finding my own strength and learning how to be the best mom I can be to my sweet boy. Everyone has their own story and their own goals; just never forget to stay true to who YOU are.

#momwatts #keepingitreal #mypostpartumjourney #lululemonambassador

caption: We live in a digital day-and-age where we feel the need to be perfect ALL the time; perfect photos, with perfect captions, with perfect clothes, with perfect people. We’re all flawed individuals, and “Perfect” isn’t actually real. The enemy can never weaponize your flaws if you’ve accepted them already. @viddmedia #VIDDMedia #DavidsManor
comments: Love it love it love it; @pamdba thank you! 🙌🏽; Yes you have to be authentic 💯; Love this!!!;

caption: My “epiphany” moment was back in 2016 when I received my first invitation to NYFW—an event I’d only dreamed of going to as a child. I had launched my blog only 2 months prior, and the thought of any designer finding value in my outlet was far beyond my own comprehension at the time. I remember sitting in my Uber ride, en route to the venue, and my whole body vigorously shaking. My body was having an actual physical reaction to the gut-wrenching anxiety I had, because I truly believed that I was going to arrive to the venue and discover that it was all just a scam. Sometimes in life, we self-sabotage our own blessings when we aren’t able to comprehend them. Some things aren’t meant for us to understand. Some paths aren’t made for us to know. I remember leaving NYFW that day, and for the first time in my life, truly believing that ANYTHING was possible. 🙏🏽 #VIDDMedia #DavidsManor @viddmedia

caption: Good Morning 🖤it’s 5:30 and I’m waking up for the day in my snow leopard onesie (I have a thing for snow leopards 😁)Just popping in to say hi. I’ve been stretching my abilities a bit between an e-workbook series, website, branding, amazon pre-launch, working out, influencer collabs, live streaming, and a life? 😆well that’s just a normal day right now 😁 crazy? Yes. It takes a level of crazy - and I love and welcome it with open arms. 🙌🏼I can’t tell you just ONE thing that drives me. There are many. I’m obsessed with thinking about creative branding ideas, I live for it. I’m obsessed with helping people, I’m the friend people go to for advice. I get a high on pushing myself past what I used to think I could handle and prove I’m capable of doing more. I’m in that messy middle between starting - complete and instead of fighting the process I’m embracing it. Let me tell you something - just try going ham on a goal for 3-4 days and see how the momentum starts to build in you. It’s the start that’s the hardest - after the momentum in flow state will start to carry you and you’ll LOVE the results you see. In any goal you have. Even if it’s a learning curve, celebrate that. Setbacks, celebrate them you’re one step CLOSER. Celebrate it all because in a week, a month, a year your mind will be blown at how much you can do just by taking steps day by day. I’m probably rambling, and it’s early but I care about you whoever you are - people like you are the reason I want to create tools to help people launch 🚀 their dream and live their life they want to live it. Oh and one more thing, don’t wait to be happy. Find joy in everyday. For me it’s writing a random note to you in a onesie by my fireplace with a cup of coffee. 🥰 have a great day friends

caption:
FEELINGS don’t matter.💀👏🏻
I know you’re thinking what?!? Feelings are everything!!! Let me clarify, you matter, but your feelings are often a shitty measurement for happiness and living the life you desire to live. Just because you feel a certain way doesn’t mean that it is reality. Just because you love someone, doesn’t mean they love you back. Just because you’re anxious about work, doesn’t mean you are doomed to fail. What WILL CAUSE you to FAIL is relying on your feelings as a whole. Guess what? I don’t feel like working out 8/10 times. But I do. I don’t feel like reading. But I do. I don’t feel like eating healthy, but I do most of the time. I don’t feel like talking on the phone, but for whoever I’m calling it does more for them than it does for me. I don’t feel like working. But I do. I don’t feel like keeping my mouth shut to keep the peace, but I have. When you realize that YOU dictate how your day goes, based on how you respond to it and WHAT you do, not how you FEEL you will be so empowered. Don’t get stuck in feelings. Don’t get stuck in anxiety. Don’t get stuck in sadness and let it lead you to a road of nothing but pain and turmoil. You have to make a decision EVERYDAY to do the work regardless of how you feel. Loving someone is a decision. Loving yourself is a decision. Doing the work regardless is a decision. Sitting sad and empty because you decided to feel like crap, is a decision. I’m deciding to feel good based on my future and the things I have to be grateful for RIGHT NOW. Sure, sad emotions and down times happen, but I’m not a victim and I don’t stay knocked down. I make a decision to get up every day and focus on the things that FEEL good. Don’t let your feelings lie to you. Don’t let them keep you down. You have a million reasons and excuses you can use to feel like crap, and you have a million reasons to feel amazing and excited for life. It’s UP TO YOU. Start living based on your decisions and not getting stuck in a feeling. Your life will drastically transform when you do. 💯

caption: ◼️Feeling stuck? Fall in love with learning. Anytime I feel as though I’m stalling, I dive into YouTube videos, books, podcasts, whatever I can get my hands on. Often times we create this imaginary glass ceiling because we fail to progress. Then anxiety hits. We feel helpless. “I want to do so many things but how and where do I begin?!” 💡Knowledge is free everywhere. Literally EVERYWHERE. We have no excuse except freezing in our own fear. Anything you or I want to do...guess what it’s probably been done. Guess what else? It’s likely easy to find someone already doing it. I’ve been watching videos and learning online from people for years doing the very thing I’m working on to do. You don’t need to reinvent the wheel. You can REFINE it though. But don’t stall in stress in anxiety and accomplish nothing. To do lists feel great, but they require actually doing them to reach the goal. You’re NOT STUCK. You’re NOT BEHIND. Shake that $hit off! Get excited by listening to others! Find mentors online if you can’t in person. Create momentum every morning with a growth grind. I talk to my group on @jasmindotcom about this all the time. It requires a morning routine. And often times, I don’t feel like doing it. I don’t always FEEL excited and ready to go. But once I start DOING, the feeling comes. One thing I’ve learned from successful entrepreneurs, they are always learning. So if you feel stuck, get up and exercise, listen to something to move your body and your mind. Make this a daily practice. If nothing else, today you’ll know more than you did yesterday. And that’s not being stuck, that’s progress. And progress is a great place to start🔥

#TBT at Cafe Gratitude💚I’ve been emotional eating randomly. It doesn’t mean over eating, just in ways that aren’t healthy in general. So I’m currently on a juice cleanse to reset. Guess what - I struggle too! And if you feel like you can’t live without something, try giving it up a week and see how you feel. I use stevia like it’s going to become extinct. The problem with sweeteners, even if they say low glycemic index (doesn’t spike blood sugars) they still mess with your body and can cause weight gain if you use them too much. When you eat something sweet your body is waiting on sugar to digest. When it doesn’t get it, even if it claims it doesn’t -it can mess with blood sugar levels and spike cravings. I realized I was hardly eating but always hungry, and eating more “healthy junk food” than ever. So learn to listen to your body. Give up caffeine, alcohol, sugar, sweeteners, for a short time and see how it resets your taste, energy and mind. This is not fun for me. I thrive on coffee and stevia. Stevia is great, when in pure form. But don’t get it mixed with dextrose, or sugar, on accident like I did. (I may as well be eating cake all day 🤦🏻‍♀️). And too much of it can affect your hormones. Do you have something that isn’t necessarily bad but you may be over eating it? Do a literal gut check. If you’re tired, bloated, and hungry all the time it’s a sign something is off. I’ll add the organic version back in moderation later when I feel great again. Until then celery juice and matcha tea takes its place. Have a good day friends! 🍎☺️

caption:
Sponsored by Galderma @restylaneusa

Do you #KysseAndTell🤫? With Galderma's newest lip filler, Restylane®Kysse ~ now I do 👄!

As Editor-in-Chief of Average Socialite, every summer I head to the Hamptons to cover some amazing events. Like most women, I want to look my best on & off camera. In recent years I’ve noticed volume loss in my lips as well as fine lines. I heard about injectable fillers which are used to help decrease the signs of aging, including shape or volume loss & fine lines above the upper lip; while increasing the size & shape of your lips in order to make them even & balanced.

One of my main concerns about getting lip filler was maintaining a natural look & feel. That’s why I was excited to meet @drdendy & learn about RestylaneKysse ~ the newest hyaluronic acid lip filler from @GaldermaaestheticaUSA. RestylaneKysse provides natural-looking, fuller lips for patients over the age of 21, & lasts for up to 1 year! (1-3)

My appointment with Dr. Dendy was on a Thursday afternoon. Dr. Dendy had a look at my lips & really liked the shape, so she focused on enhancing their size. After numbing my lips, the procedure was quick & painless.

I couldn't be happier with my results! My lips look & feel so natural with just the right amount of volume. My fine lines above my upper lip also disappeared. Here I am ~ just 3 days after my treatment ~ relaxing at the beach with my family. Click the link in my bio for up to $100 off Restylane Kysse & to sign-up for ASPIRE rewards.

The most commonly observed side effects are swelling, tenderness, bruising, pain, & redness at the injection site. To learn more about serious but rare side effects & full Important Safety Information, visit www.RestylaneUSA.com

caption:
Some days I miss being pregnant 🤰🏻⁣
⁣
Don’t get me wrong, I am nowhere close to wanting to be pregnant again right now Haha but there are some things I miss like feeling her kick & just that happy glow when you know a sweet baby is on their way. ⁣
⁣
Last night I finally wrote a blog post about my 2nd trimester! I know, it’s months later & I still have to & want to write about my 3rd trimester, what to put in your hospital bag (I never put one together in time! More on that later!) and Violet’s birth story which I haven’t told yet. There are so many things I feel I haven’t been on top of as someone who wants to blog & be a content creator and “influencer.” So many things I feel like I’ve failed at or it’s too late to write about. However I still want to write about these things because I think its helpful to those who are also expecting and even therapeutic for me to tell my story. ⁣
⁣
Since becoming a mom I haven’t been as active as I want to be on here because I’m just trying to survive honestly! I’ve also been getting help for postpartum depression which I also want to share about and I think I’m starting to feel the clouds lift. 

As I was writing my second trimester recap I was feeling guilty about how long it’s taken me to even write this post & as I was going through my journal I realized that during my 2nd trimester is when the Coronavirus started to take hold of the world. I had lost my job, I was almost 7 months pregnant & I started to realize I couldn’t be with my friends of family. That’s when I realized why I never started my 2nd trimester blog post. The world seemed to be falling apart & I along with it. 😥 A lot of the hope of being pregnant was taken over by fear and sadness. So even though I might have felt a little ashamed that I didn’t write a 2nd trimester blog post in a timely manner (I’m very hard on my self) I had to give myself grace and compassion to remember what I was going through at the time and what I’m still going through. 

So if you check out my newest blog post (link in bio!) just know it was very cathartic for me to post & let me know in the comments how your life has changed these past few crazy months 💕📸by @katiedayphotography

caption:
Let’s talk: CBD ✨

Does anyone else struggle with falling asleep quickly? For me, I always seem to be up because I just can’t stop thinking. About what I need to do tomorrow, that song that’s stuck in my head, or something embarrassing that happened in 3rd grade 😂 

For that reason, I try to be intentional with setting myself up for restful sleep. 

Some things I’ve tried include melatonin, essential oils, supplements, etc. but lately I figured I would give @socialcbd sleep gummies go and see how I liked them! They’re a blend of essential oils, natural herbs, and CBD. 

BACKSTORY: I have always been wary of CBD just because it’s also derived from the hemp plant—but no worries, CBD contains no THC (the psychoactive ingredient).

Anywhoooo, I’ve been trying them out on and off for about a month, so here are a few thoughts! 

-relaxing, not overly drowsy 
-gummies are easy to take without water
-not a huuuuge fan of the flavor, but no biggie 
-seem to wake up much less when taking them 
-not drowsy in the morning, either (some people feel like they can’t wake up after taking melatonin) 

Have you ever tried melatonin, CBD, or anything else for sleep? What works for you?

caption:
Reminder: don’t stretch yourself too thin this next week (like this here slinky)! 🧡

What’s on your plate over the next week? Mine involves doing some shoots for various clients, school assignments, and other work stuff!

I tend to spread myself thin often. Take your Sunday to reflect on your goals for the next week, and where your time and energy should go! 

Just ask yourself the question: what is my ultimate goal? Are the tasks I’m filling my days with helping me get there? 

Your ultimate goal could be to own your own business. To have your own family. To work in a field you’re passionate about. Whatever it is, don’t lose sight of that long-term goal. 

With that in mind, don’t get too caught  up over the little things. You don’t have to take you every opportunity you’re presented with. It’s okay to pass up events, to have a messy house every now and then, to fail an exam. Chances are those will have little effect in the long run :) 

With that being said, TAKE IT EASY ON YOURSELF. Set realistic expectations and enjoy the journey! Trust that our Maker will get you where you need to go. 🧡

Have a wonderful Sunday, friends!

 Bella

caption:
Cupcakes are just muffins that believed in miracles 🧁 

So, I’m not usually dairy free but decided to challenge myself by making some strawberry amaretto cupcakes! I used the new @kitehillfoods European style plant based butter, which was actually pretty good! 

I can be skeptical of how dairy alternatives taste—but this was actually so yummy. It’s made with almond milk, so nothing crazy in there. 

I will say, when you make this buttercream, make sure to keep it cold and use sparingly. She can get a little soft at room temperature :) 

DAIRY FREE BUTTERCREAM 
- 1/4 cup strawberry purée (fresh berries in a food processor or blender)
- 4 cups powdered sugar 
- 1/2 cup @kitehillfoods European butter (COLD not room temp)
- 1 tsp almond extract 

Cream butter, then beat in powered sugar 1/2 cup at a time. Add strawberry purée and almond extract and beat briefly one more time. That’s all! Use immediately, and store any extras in the fridge :)

Hope you all enjoy this recipe! What’s your fav cupcake flavor? I imagine you could add just about any flavor in the place of the ones I did and it would be tasty! 

Xoxo,

Bella

caption:
Who do you love in your life who might be pretty “different” from you?

When we started dating, we realized that we are...very different! 

I laugh at it now. For a moment though, I let it psych me out. “Will we have similar interests? Will we want the same things? What about our careers?” I thought. 

I’m a student, very creative and ambitious. I sing and dance in public for fun. He works full time in ministry (for @thefcateam), is a morning bird, and is a chill, sweet, lowkey guy. I love fashion, he is a sports man through and through! 

However, what became very apparent is that our different hobbies and lifestyles weren’t stumbling blocks. Our differences compliment each other’s. If we were copies of each other, we would have the same weak spots and strengths! 

If we had passed each other up on account of being “too different” we would have been MAJORLY missing out! 

What matters for us is that we both have the same desire—to chase after the Lord. We’re able to do that together which is such a blessing! 

Willis has amazing character that I truly admire. He is kind, extremely generous, intentional with his relationships and silly. The Lord only makes those qualities stronger and better as he grows with God!

Character > Commonalities ❤️

caption:
A WORD ON DISAPPOINTMENT 👏🏻 

Last week, I learned I was not selected for an internship at my school that—in my mind—I was even OVER qualified for. 

I was a little frustrated—they were asking for an on-camera social media intern, as well as two behind the scenes interns. 

I have been concentrated on social media marketing for three years. I employ myself in freelance content creation. I’m an “influencer” so to speak—and that comes with skills that would prep me for this position!

I’m not trying to hype myself up here, but more so just wanted to open up about what disappointment can look like. These are the things that go on behind the scenes, that don’t usually get revealed when you’re just scrolling through your feed!

I’ve had to learn that “no’s” are often a gift—leading us to where we ACTUALLY belong. I’m confident that time that I could have spent in that internship will be better used elsewhere, leading me to where I’m supposed to be!

What’s a disappointment or “no” you’ve had to deal with? Where did you end up instead? 

Love always,

Bella

caption:
It’s extremely scary when a loved one gets diagnosed with cancer. It’s flooring when it’s your dad at age 53. It was one month before my 1st Ironman that I’d dreamt of since a little girl. Through his treatments and surgery, I told my dad I’m staying by your and mom’s side; I’ll put everything on hold. My dad said in Spanish: “mija, your goal is my goal. Your hope is my hope. You do this and I promise you I’ll be at that finish line for you.” This moment remains special because my dad remains cancer-free and each day is a blessing. 

This November, I’m helping #StopCancerB4ItStarts by running the #PreventCancer5k. When you register for $25 and/or fundraise, your registration proceeds are donated and contribute to @preventcancer programs such as: education, advocacy, outreach, and research. Learn more at #preventcancer.org

caption:
just jumpin on the bed and doin a happy dance. ✨⁣
⁣
what a week. lots of emotions that led up to today 🖤 AND i have an exciting life update i’ve been so eager to share!⁣
⁣
on monday i accepted a FULL-TIME JOB OFFER! it’s been quite the year of workplace uncertainty. if you don’t know, i have been working professionally as a graphic designer for 2 years! i somehow survived without losing any work until august, and all at once i lost my consistent freelance gig, and my design agency job dwindled down to having no work for me. it totally felt like the negative work effects of COVID happened to me in reverse order... but i was blessed to be able to jump into content creation and freelance full-time and have been doing that for about 4 months. fast forward to today, i spent the last month in the application process for what is shaping up to be the best job opportunity i’ve ever had, and that was after putting countless applications into what felt like an empty void (LinkedIn LOL). i couldn’t be more excited to start a career with a company i began a work relationship with by creating IG content for them 📸 here’s to new beginnings and a whole lotta juice 😉🧃 ⁣
⁣
as for this space, i’m not going anywhere! it will just be some restructuring — creating content on weekends, posting in the evening on weekdays, and i’m SO excited for a new experience on the app! more content for fun and less sponsored pressure 🙏🏼 always grateful for post notifications if you wanna be sure you don’t miss my posts happening at new times! ⁣
⁣
i love you all. don’t stop pushing when you have something you want; just be patient and God will give you what you ask for.

caption:
In this town, we call home, everyone hail to the pumpkin song 🎃💀✨ 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Welcome to Halloween Town my friends!! I took the #FreeformHalloweenRoad to get there this year & it was nothing short of spooktacular!  Every year, @freeform hosts a fun Halloween event to kick start their @31nightsofhalloween , in which they play your favorite Halloween movies for you to enjoy all October long! 🤩🎃👻✨ 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For this years event, @freeform transformed their typical Halloween House into a Halloween Road, in which visitors can drive through themed areas from the safety of their own car! I think @freeform did an INCREDIBLE job putting this event together so that it is organized, safe, and SO MUCH FUN! 👻 We were able to coast through The Nightmare Before Christmas’s Halloween Town, Sanderson’s Cottage, & even spot the Ghostbusters! 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Another awesome touch was that they even added areas for Trick or Treating!!! Again, it was very creative & totally safe! Same thing with photo ops!! Swipe to the end to see how they still found a way for us to get that iconic shot on top of The Spiral Hill... it’s the best 😂♥️💀🎃✨ 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thank you @freeform for inviting me to this unforgettable experience! I’m so ready to tune into @31nightsofhalloween & finally embrace this spooky season! What are some of your favorite Halloween movies? 🎃🍿

caption:
October 1st-31st, 2020

To Participate:
1. Share a photo of you in your Casual Cosplay on Instagram 

2. Use hashtags #31DaysofCasualCosplay & #CasualCosplayBook

3. Tag @krystaleverdeen in the photo & caption

*New posts only
*Prompts / themes TBA - please check stories! 

In order to be considered to be in the book, follow these guidelines in addition to the ones outlined above:
– Photos cannot contain 3rd party trademarks (No logos, brand names, etc.)

– Photos cannot be taken in theme parks

 – Participant must be 18+ years of age

– Photo must be shared anytime between October 1st - October 27th, 2020

– If reached out to regarding being in the book, participant must be willing to sign a Release Form that allows author and publisher to use photo in the book as well as marketing material

– Release Forms must be signed and submitted to Krystal Everdeen by October 28, 2020

These rules only apply to those submitting photos for a chance to be in the book, but anyone can participate in 31 Days of Casual Cosplay; whether you are under the age of 18 or have taken photos at the parks, I would still love to see your looks! Thank you again for all your love and support! 🎃✨

Music by @ericreprid - Palace via @hellothematic

caption:
Dreamy, far-off look & her nose stuck in a book 📖🌹✨

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Growing up, I had always enjoyed reading & writing. However, never in my wildest dreams would I have thought I would write my own book. So today, I am incredibly thrilled announce that... I’m an AUTHOR! 📚 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ve combined my love for writing with my love for character inspired fashion to bring you my first book, Casual Cosplay! ✨ In this book, I teach you how to put together outfits that resemble your favorite characters with pieces you may already have in your closet! I share outfit ideas featuring basics I believe nearly everyone already owns, as well as more advanced & creative examples! 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you love dressing up & theming your outfits off of characters, this book is perfect for you! Speaking of you, how would YOU like to be in my book?? This October, I will be hosting 31 Days of Casual Cosplay, in which I will be sharing a new casual cosplay every day in October! Participate by sharing a photo of you in your casual cosplay, tagging me & using the hashtags #31daysofcasualcosplay & #CasualCosplayBook 

  ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I will be sharing everyone’s looks on my stories & possibly reaching out to some of you for the chance to be in my book! 😄🙌🏻 For more details, please watch my latest YouTube video, link in bio! I’ve already had the honor of having amazing friends & talented creators be a part of my book, & I am so excited for you to be a part of it as well! 🥰✨

caption:
Dreaming of a land far, far way ✨

And hey, I’ve noticed a few new faces here, & I wanted to say Hi! 😄✨ My name is Krystal Everdeen & I enjoy sharing character inspired outfit ideas on my YouTube channel! And yes, I’m addition to Disney, I also love Star Wars, Harry Potter, Lord of the Ring & more! What about you? I would love to see you there ☺️✨ Also, trust me, I’m not just randomly letting you know all of this, it will tie in later 😉 Because.... caption:

Channeling my inner Air Nomad 🌀 Are you a fan of ATLA? I sure am! Some may even say I’m kind of obsessed with with it haha 🥰 Fun fact, Flying Bison are actually my favorite animals! I have so many plushies, pins, & prints of them, that I’ve made it official-they’re my favorite 🙌🏻

 And what’s funny is that I never really realized how big my ATLA collection was until I filmed my Avatar the Last Airbender collection -which is now live on my YouTube channel btw 😉- & what’s even funnier is that I’ve already added 7 new items to my collection since filming that video 😅 Clearly, my love for this show is strong🔥🌊💨🌎 #avatarthelastairbender #atla

caption:

caption:
Be careful — this pie has a BITE to it.
🥧 One of my favorite scary movies is The Mummy (1999). I know, I know, it's not that scary... but it's pretty much my limit. I’ve never made any recipes or DIY projects inspired by The Mummy, which is a real missed opportunity in my opinion. So, this Halloween season, I *attempted* to remedy that. 
Key word = attempted. 🥴
You see, I had this idea to make a scarab pie. You know, those incredibly creepy, cringe-worthy, and flesh-eating beetles from The Mummy. And it just turned out kinda creepy... I'm not sure if that's a good or bad thing. ‼️ Lesson -- bugs don't make good pie decorations. 🤷🏻‍♀️
